[R38] {'review_id': 'h_Wgc_YzHHW02B7cqF_YOw', 'user_id': 'aEHO6VeU84w45eNTBLCEzw', 'business_id': '2BRbu3cBbH2bCgzN3DVc8w', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I am surprised at the below 3 stars rating because I've eaten here twice and everything is very well prepared, nicely served, and delicious. However with that said, the young waiter we had seemed a little too anxious in increasing our bill with with drinks and an expensive bottle of Pelligrino that could have been drank by about 5 people. There were only two of us. We sent it back . When will center city restaurants stop gouging it's customers by serving huge bottles of expensive sparkling water? We just want a nice personal bottle of Perrier sometimes. The place is definitely worth a 3 star for sure", 'date': '2012-03-13 20:39:56', 'user': {'name': 'Tom', 'review_count': 22, 'yelping_since': '2010-08-12 02:45:56', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.5, 'fans': 4}}
[R39] {'review_id': 'Ip_P9qVzgoQ6mNmje8QRLQ', 'user_id': '5G2IF0VIN3Brl-m45QDXsA', 'business_id': '2BRbu3cBbH2bCgzN3DVc8w', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Why, oh why does this place have bad ratings? Loved it.  Came here for a biz lunch and I can't wait to come back in the spring when their outdoor space is open for dining and drinking.  They bring out bread and an amazing red pepper and oil spread to start you off.  I ordered the Insalata Funghi..delicious salad that comes with a black truffle vinaigarette that is absolutely to DIE for..tomatoes, mushrooms, mixed greens and shaved parm.  In. L.O.V.E.  My dining partners got the Cobb Salad (it looked decent) and the sirloin burger with cheddar cheese and carmelized onions.  I almost climbed across the table to get a bite, but of course that's not appropriate in any case. So I refrained.  I will be back so so so soon! Only reason why this place gets 4 stars and not 5 is that it's pricey..$70+ for a 3 person lunch..plus tip.  Either way, great scene for business and/or personal dining.", 'date': '2012-03-07 22:31:46', 'user': {'name': 'Alie', 'review_count': 327, 'yelping_since': '2011-12-08 22:14:07', 'elite': '2012,2013', 'average_stars': 3.97, 'fans': 45}}
[R40] {'review_id': '1tML7iMpxNpHfGrgk5JiQQ', 'user_id': 'JJk49Bp27Def-IIYIwHSkw', 'business_id': '2BRbu3cBbH2bCgzN3DVc8w', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'My 2nd spot for dinner during restaurant week. The food was okay; my appetizer of artichoke ravioli was delicious and the homemade cookie plate was just the right amount of sweet. For my entree I chose the wild striped bass; the fish was cooked perfectly but the potatoes and asparagus could have left off the plate. I probably would not go back for dinner but I think I would check this spot out in the spring for happy hour.', 'date': '2012-02-02 14:39:44', 'user': {'name': 'christina', 'review_count': 263, 'yelping_since': '2010-03-12 21:59:33', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.44, 'fans': 10}}
