[R43] {'review_id': '-HALNYzPQgtabgtbeL2_WQ', 'user_id': 'FgX-L-iA-vu6zXdcsoz6eg', 'business_id': '2BRbu3cBbH2bCgzN3DVc8w', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I went with a large group during restaurant week. The food was great for the price. I enjoyed it all. I got the salmon app (but I substituted the potato salad for just regular salad), the seared salmon, and the budino. I tried the hazelnut cake too. My main criticism is that EVERYTHING IS TOOOO OILY,BUTTERY, AND SUGARY! It is really tasty food, but I think anytime you add that much oil, butter, and sugar food HAS to be good. I actually had a coating inside my mouth I think from all the excess. That being said, I really did think my food was well cooked, especially the salmon main dish, which I would never normally get, but I wanted the barlotto and didn't want to be "that girl" that keeps switching the menu around. The hazelnut cake was more of a ganache on a hazelnut crust which was quite tasty. My friend's risotto was waaay to creamy and almost soup like, but again very good. I would also like to say the wait staff was very nice and I enjoyed the ambiance. We were upstairs and it was not too loud.', 'date': '2012-01-28 13:06:55', 'user': {'name': 'Axl', 'review_count': 187, 'yelping_since': '2011-01-26 19:48:52', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.43, 'fans': 3}}
