[R9] {'review_id': 'yNQXN6MeER-wf0p1HOKchA', 'user_id': 'qkd6LJK7HIdzagRLQpxW5A', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Frank. If we didn\'t love the restaurant so much we would come just for him. He truly makes this more than just a restaurant, it is a complete experience. The food is always great, the hospitality is one of a kind and we bring every visitor who comes into town to "our spot." My only apprehension in leaving five stars is that now everyone will come. We want Frank all to ourselves.', 'date': '2021-10-22 23:40:21', 'user': {'name': 'Melissa', 'review_count': 17, 'yelping_since': '2013-03-14 17:54:56', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.88, 'fans': 0}}
[R10] {'review_id': 'PzklpgMnIqa2DwU38_aGXQ', 'user_id': 'qSile_HpfR-LIrFgjRJ0rg', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I can't believe it took me this long to eat here. Went for my father-in-law's birthday dinner and loved every minute of it. Everything we had, from the octopus salad to the braciole to the gnocchi, was just the way you'd want it.\n\nVery cool atmosphere, too... whimsical and intimate. Reminds me of a more laid-back version of the basement at 21 Club... relaxed dress code, service that's more warm than obsequious.\n\nWill definitely come back the next time I'm in Philly.", 'date': '2021-10-05 12:58:48', 'user': {'name': 'Justin', 'review_count': 52, 'yelping_since': '2010-01-20 20:56:45', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.38, 'fans': 3}}
[R11] {'review_id': 'ck1V_qPBRr3E4aqwvmy3Gw', 'user_id': '-_Lfm5bztNCYXaBmrqY7tA', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Its been many years since I dined here. I must say things have changed a lot, good and not so good. \nLet's start with the food and drinks. They have a fantastic selection of items, and specials on the menu.  From escarole soup to steak and lobster. They also have a very enticing dessert tray! I tried the veal piccante. It was very tender and tasted quite lovely. We also tried the langostinas, they were on the specials menu. Also very well prepared, presented, and delicious. All the main dishes are a la carte. Sides include sauteed spinach, mashed potatoes, sauteed escarole, and there was also a brussel sprout side added. There are two bars, one upstairs and one on the main dining area as you walk in. The bars are beautiful and well stocked.  They have a decent wine and cocktail menu.  I decided to try the Vesper, it was very good! \nWhat's changed? The price of food here is very high! Too high for the area, the type of cuisine (Italian), and for a casual restaurant not known for great cuisine made by well known chefs. There are many top restaurants in the city with comparable pricing, or lower. It would be quite a challenge to dine here again simply based on the very high priced items.  Please take this into consideration! \nBread.  Not good at all! Our bread came out in a small basket and was frozen in the center. Appeared to have been warmed up very quickly. It was not fresh or tasty.  In fact, this almost ruined my appetite.  I didn't mention this to the server because I had already decided this was not typical or satisfactory; and I didn't really need to eat bread that badly anyway. \nComplementary parking.  They have a couple lots to park at.  They were both full.  However there is a valet that will park your car. He will let you know he works for tips. Be good to him. I would recommend taking a taxi, Uber/Lyft to the restaurant..  It would save you time and the aggravation of driving around trying to find a parking space, or tipping the friendly valet. \nSaloon has beautiful old world decor.  Lots of beautiful carved wood and nice artwork throughout.  To be quite frank, it's a little too busy.  The restaurant is very clean.  The service was very good! Everyone here is well dressed and appeared to enjoy doing their job.  They were very welcoming from entering and leaving. \nOverall, Saloon was a disappointment, despite being a traditional South Philly landmark. I was not happy with the prices here at all. Especially since it was a la carte. I probably won't come back, but I feel you should at least give it a try, take your chances. Be prepared to spend at least $70 or more per person.  There's too many other Italian restaurants in the city I would recommend on all levels.", 'date': '2021-10-02 13:24:37', 'user': {'name': 'Ray', 'review_count': 174, 'yelping_since': '2011-10-04 20:56:56', 'elite': '2015,2016,2021', 'average_stars': 4.26, 'fans': 14}}
[R12] {'review_id': 'ny_pyywXCt39XUFOtq8ZFA', 'user_id': '5jKScvMqxW_rzd0D8xgX1A', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Came here with my family and had blast! Our server was amazing and everyone was so friendly.  They def had a huge specials selection which was hard to remember but sounded so good.  We ordered a combination of pasta, seafood and meat and we really enjoyed everything. I dont think you can go wrong with anything here.', 'date': '2021-09-30 17:22:57', 'user': {'name': 'Mike', 'review_count': 271, 'yelping_since': '2011-06-23 20:30:28', 'elite': '2014,2015,2016,2017', 'average_stars': 4.29, 'fans': 9}}
[R13] {'review_id': 'BZ5CPMuhx-XSiScLhED1gg', 'user_id': 'oK03j2HvvGTJ2Y_QbLU43g', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Our favorite spot.  Food is always on point and martinis are best in the city.   Can be pricey but worth it.', 'date': '2021-09-24 23:56:21', 'user': {'name': 'Ed', 'review_count': 6, 'yelping_since': '2015-11-23 12:42:44', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.64, 'fans': 0}}
[R14] {'review_id': 't-hwwFVh08e24WvEL6ocIA', 'user_id': '-wksA6A9WjBk0t906rPLbw', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I regret not having taken pictures of the food but it was to die for. I hadn't seen my ex since 2015 and I figured that The Saloon was the spot for a fresh restart. We shared the Clams Pavarotti which she loved and with good reason. They were divine. I had the Truffle Filet (a special) which had a crust on the surface and pure meat butter on the inside. I ate this slowly savoring every morsel.  This restaurant has always maintained the highest level of quality for so long. It's old school South Philly refinement and class makes one feel like she walked into a time machine where everyone dresses to the nines and feels that he is part of something. We had such a wonderful time there. I give it a 4.85 with a miniscule deduction for not getting the freshest bread. MADONE!", 'date': '2021-09-18 21:23:55', 'user': {'name': 'David', 'review_count': 9, 'yelping_since': '2018-09-06 20:49:34', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.44, 'fans': 0}}
[R15] {'review_id': '4x3YRnxMBNP9lIVIiEy6fg', 'user_id': 'WtnerGVQjEgJHNM2rnJDEg', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I have been here many times. The valet parking is free and extremely convenient. The restaurant's decor is gorgeous, lots of wood and leather. The drinks are strong and the food is tasty but certainly nothing special with the occasional surprise. The upstairs bar  gets noisy. The total experience is more luxurious than 3 stars, but definitely not a five star resto. So 4 stars.", 'date': '2021-09-16 22:43:43', 'user': {'name': 'David', 'review_count': 98, 'yelping_since': '2009-03-15 21:00:53', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.53, 'fans': 0}}
[R16] {'review_id': 'VyVtJu8W2LSozM91pfV6ew', 'user_id': 'AK30CGAECtE_7GwCmDMMMA', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'My husband and I had an excellent dinner at the Saloon last PM.  We started off with "The Sampler", Poblano Stuffed Peppers, Clams Casino, Clams Pavorotti, and Langostinos.  This was a fabulous appetizer!  For dinner, my husband had Veal Parm with the best homemade raviolis ever!  I had the Lobster Francaise, with Broccoli Rabe,  Beans and Sausage. Our cocktails were spot on and OMG, I almost forgot to mention the bread and pesto. The pesto is homemade and hands down the best I\'ve ever had aside from my future daughter in law\'s This Resturant is a "must visit" when we are in the city. \n\nI have to give a shout out to our server Amy.  She was so sweet, kind and beautiful. She not only remembered serving us 3 weeks ago when we dined there but she knew exactly what we had including our drinks. Now that\'s impressive!!  She knows the menu well and when she goes over the specials with you she describes them in such a way that you want to have one of each. Thank you Amy for your excellent service and we look forward to seeing you again soon.\n\nKim & Scott G.', 'date': '2021-09-13 01:32:56', 'user': {'name': 'Kim', 'review_count': 12, 'yelping_since': '2012-12-22 15:29:06', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R17] {'review_id': 'uZPEHDD0MOZ7y9qODsLrFQ', 'user_id': 'DwshcLeRbQzyo-RP1WK5XA', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This was my first time eating here and I was excited as I've heard about it a lot. To be honest it exceeded my expectations which were not the highest, it was a fantastic dinner and I look forward to going back. I did not even realize they had free valet parking which was . \n\nTomatoes and crab starter was top notch.", 'date': '2021-08-02 23:52:22', 'user': {'name': 'M', 'review_count': 35, 'yelping_since': '2012-07-31 18:53:52', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.61, 'fans': 0}}
[R18] {'review_id': 'naZr1AyPRSOm0MnQQMH1kQ', 'user_id': 's7xEAffNcf_4XG156aAxmw', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Delish!! Food was outstanding and service was excellent! I love the atmosphere of this place reminds me of the 1920's or something all the dark wood and tile. Lovely place can't wait to go back", 'date': '2021-05-26 11:36:06', 'user': {'name': 'Heather', 'review_count': 38, 'yelping_since': '2012-12-30 21:12:24', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.05, 'fans': 0}}
[R19] {'review_id': 'PLDm8XnLZXj-hbyHhjWJRA', 'user_id': 'cHxPxdA4Y4M5S7d0gJf6MA', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Amazing that the food is still excellent, but the waitresses stink. They use to be a main attraction, for both looks and service.  The waiters are better now except for the one who is ok with you substituting what you may not want, for a charged side dish.  The interior is fabulous.  Pricing has gotten better offering good value for high quality product and perfect execution.  Service should be more professional, as it will keep me away for a while.', 'date': '2021-05-21 18:28:26', 'user': {'name': 'Jerry', 'review_count': 40, 'yelping_since': '2009-10-07 12:20:26', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.53, 'fans': 1}}
[R20] {'review_id': 'AvK1Z8XiIIeF3atUR9D__g', 'user_id': 'Io3IpnLC3dTnfxPrCzdGvw', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'The food here is DELISH! We got:\n\n- bread (free and excellent), \n- tuna sashimi appetizer (excellent), \n- caesar salad (not incredible), \n- bragiole (holy shit that was so goddamn delish) \n- lobster fettuccine (pasta was overcooked and soft) \n- gluten free spaghetti (not terrible, which is a win for GF!!) \n- berry tart (not incredible) \n- almond cake (wayy better than expected) \n\nHope this helps someone!', 'date': '2021-05-10 14:09:45', 'user': {'name': 'Matthew', 'review_count': 70, 'yelping_since': '2013-06-19 21:12:58', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.33, 'fans': 3}}
[R21] {'review_id': 'sXpQ3nEybcN-i-R-FWDpUA', 'user_id': 'eQrqy9t2ciHNtdwVHQXRxw', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "In my 4 years living in South philly, having tried what I thought was all the best Italian spots, we had never made our way into Saloon. Until last night. Wow. What a remarkable place. First they hit you with two giant free parking lots. Get outta town that's unheard of in the city. Walking into the restaurant, the vibes and ambiance are way more than expected. Our group had the opportunity of sitting at a beautiful semi-private table surrounded by glass windows. Truly made the experience top level. The service was out of this world as well. Not a water glass waiting to be filled or a cocktail left empty. Huge shout out to FRANK and ALYSSA for making our dinner amazing. Frank (who I have definitely seen in the series Boardwalk Empire), was such a genuine and fun loving guy. He put a smile on our faces every time he came by. Now for the food - unreal. So amazing. We ordered the truffle steak and i have never had a piece of meat melt in my mouth the way that did. Washed it down with some mashed potatoes, some arugula/pear/and burrata salad, with just enough room for lava cake and berry cobbler. Overall I would give it a 13/10. And will be back...maybe even later today", 'date': '2021-04-10 12:06:34', 'user': {'name': 'Andy', 'review_count': 4, 'yelping_since': '2019-10-17 01:54:45', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R22] {'review_id': 'wwJfbNs7d3reI98LEMM9XA', 'user_id': 'KNQz__F64qvKPOxeXPc9Ag', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Four "immunized" boomers decided to have our first dine-in experience in a year at The Saloon.  And are we glad we did!  Covid protocols were in place but most importantly, the food was exceptional --as one would expect from this Philly icon. Our server was vivacious and the manager even made a fuss over two of us who had birthdays that week. A wonderful, memorable night. Grazie!', 'date': '2021-03-22 17:49:02', 'user': {'name': 'Marianne', 'review_count': 28, 'yelping_since': '2015-07-18 15:24:57', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.41, 'fans': 0}}
[R23] {'review_id': 'RO6Ek5EaRPfaImwwHa1q8g', 'user_id': 'BXBtET2Kk7MmsqEXYySXtg', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 2, 'text': 'Saloon is an amazing experience. Everything about it is just so old school and traditional Italian. From the menu offerings to the actual decor (big wooden bar that spans a sizeable part of the restaurant as soon as you walk in, lots of dark and rich tones in the furniture, and of course the food being served on multiple floors just fills the building with the irresistible Italian cuisine aroma.)\n\nIt is in the heart of South Philly, always crowded with great people. Love the energy in this restaurant. \n\nYou are going to spend some decent money here, it can be a bit pricey if you are just seeking Italian food, but in my opinion, it is all worth it!', 'date': '2021-02-22 17:42:18', 'user': {'name': 'Vincent', 'review_count': 206, 'yelping_since': '2020-01-28 03:25:01', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.96, 'fans': 11}}
[R24] {'review_id': 'bCVZW9mCXygnL0Siaj0eHg', 'user_id': 'qifgGoyS3Fnt7KogFa064Q', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "LOVE this restaurant. I mean everything about it is amazing and perfect. We've been here about 5 different times and I have gotten consistent amazing service and food every single time. To start, the ambiance of this restaurant gives you 1960s vibes with the old decor, unique layout and a very impressive upstairs dining area. I also really appreciate the free parking lot they provide since parking in south Philly can be a pain. The food here is simply next level. Everything I've gotten has come out fresh, flavorful, and amazing. Portions are very generous and good for sharing. Service overall is top notch. They do not rush you to order and eat and leave like some places. They allow to you get your drinks and take your time before food comes out so you can enjoy the atmosphere. Overall this is one of my favorite restaurants in the city. I recommend making reservations because they get packed.", 'date': '2021-02-13 14:24:22', 'user': {'name': 'Hang', 'review_count': 37, 'yelping_since': '2015-04-23 18:22:00', 'elite': '2021', 'average_stars': 3.97, 'fans': 0}}
[R25] {'review_id': 'UvKwPUFODhRXma2afMvTAw', 'user_id': '5NsB7O10FRrrHVAP1Z9RnQ', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I cannot express, how good Saloon is - but I'll try. If you're looking for the perfect old school, South Philly, date night spot this is IT. \n\nWe have a few couple friends that we've been here a few times with and I have never been disappointed. If you, and once indoor dining opens again, try to snag a seat upstairs. Everything from the red lighting to the wall decor creates the coziest setting. \n\nWe ordered two of the appetizer samplers that come with stuffed clams, veal stuffed poblano peppers, and prawns - I'd highly recommend if you want a little bit of everything (and drizzle some of the oil they give you on top - it's AMAZING!). I'm a big seafood person and always love the Crab Stuffed Salmon, but got the Scallops & Crab in Cognac sauce off their specials menu the last time we went and it was out of this world. My friend got the truffle steak and also raved about it. \n\nI'm not a huge dessert person, but you really can't go wrong with anything on their menu. And don't skip on an espresso martini to finish things off.", 'date': '2020-11-20 15:04:26', 'user': {'name': 'Kelli', 'review_count': 23, 'yelping_since': '2015-08-08 17:43:42', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.56, 'fans': 2}}
[R26] {'review_id': 'l4L8iYcPoBZmSBphYdWAzQ', 'user_id': 'CPivNJkWGNZQo2zBXrfXqQ', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We had a 60th Birthday day party for our best friend and the evening was outstanding for the food to the service I would highly recommend it !!! Petite FiletStuffed ClamsEggplant ParmChicken MelanzanaBraciole15oz. Grilled Veal Chop', 'date': '2020-10-20 06:51:55', 'user': {'name': 'Ettore', 'review_count': 32, 'yelping_since': '2012-07-30 14:31:56', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.83, 'fans': 1}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'OIQKF9tolpsHnISPc_As1A', 'user_id': 'qa3zU8C1n58xEzd1qFZP8w', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Really loved this place. Ate here a few weeks back when I was in Philly for work. The atmosphere is very chill and the decor is really neat. The food was excellent too. Carole Baskin killed her husband. I will definitely be back and highly recommend this Italian gem.', 'date': '2020-04-22 15:33:54', 'user': {'name': 'Brad', 'review_count': 10, 'yelping_since': '2015-10-01 16:38:50', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.3, 'fans': 0}}
[R28] {'review_id': 'nfBV5lKafShKH8cu9uOfWg', 'user_id': '1IBrv1Ebbk6R9KKSC8l7jQ', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I was taken to Saloon for many years as a child with my Mother, a local celebrity and with family friend Pete Pagano. In my mind I had a very fond memory. We were celebrating my friend\'s 60th birthday with early reservations on a Sat. night. We checked our coats, I remember complimenting the coat check girl (later to find was reported to be the Manager Susan\'s Niece). \nMy (extremely unique) scarf and a lapel pin (with semi precious stones)\nwas not returned with my coat!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\nNot in my entire life has this kind of thing happened. After looking throughout the coatroom (giving the thief time to place it on the floor or come up with another bs reason why it was not returned to me). I left without my belongings.\nCalling for weeks & speaking to the day manager, all I got was: "we have people checking furs. Why would my [niece] take your things, she\'s a student at the Arts Institute. My things were VERY unique & also very sentimental. \nSaloon hires thieves and they are their family and you will never get your things back.\nI\'d say DON\'T GO and if you do, keep your eyes on your stuff.\nAnd i found the food to be over sauced.\n\nI would still like you to return my belongings!!!!!!', 'date': '2020-03-29 04:51:20', 'user': {'name': 'Laurie', 'review_count': 1, 'yelping_since': '2019-07-10 21:05:18', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 1.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R29] {'review_id': '1ijV719ASH9ItuqeFR2WEg', 'user_id': 'rdp2a-7sPlqmYlYvuXGlNw', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Wonderful experience! Meal was fantastic. Drinks were perfect and service was amazing. One of the best Italian Restaurants in the city.', 'date': '2020-02-26 11:51:33', 'user': {'name': 'Eileen', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2014-12-02 00:48:50', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R30] {'review_id': 'cmomPp2kViAOvbrJMYSxoQ', 'user_id': 'zXdQqQlLHfKOkG_E_79SaA', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Great food ++++\nprices reasonable\nFree parking\nService +++++++\nDrinks were awesome\n\nHaven't been for 30 Years just as good will be going back\n\nPhil from Philly", 'date': '2020-02-23 11:54:47', 'user': {'name': 'Phil', 'review_count': 30, 'yelping_since': '2014-06-05 11:19:42', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.78, 'fans': 1}}
[R31] {'review_id': '_IFoCbPoV_u1cctxPeNAmA', 'user_id': 'VZx5bcb0yqToz8RmGSI0-Q', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Decent food, okay service and poor management.\n\nWalked in for a 8:30 reservation at 8:30 and were told "it\'ll be a few minutes". No problem we wait. 20 minutes go by and we are told "go upstairs the host up there is expecting you the tables are getting ready now". Walk up and admire all the old time decor (only cool thing about this place) only to wait another 20 minutes for the table. 40 minutes later we were seated with a "hey thanks for waiting" and that was it. For an restaurant of this level you\'d expect more from management and communication. Server was nice but dropped the check off and never saw her again, another waitress closed us out. \n\nCan definitely get the same quality food at other spots in the city. Go in for a drink at the bar if you\'re dying to see the decor. Other than that it\'s not worth your time.', 'date': '2020-02-09 14:01:06', 'user': {'name': 'Lianne', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2014-11-23 18:16:32', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.25, 'fans': 0}}
[R32] {'review_id': 'E3nLxqPCUVGHohfCEVN48Q', 'user_id': '6rLcSCokJDCpwSjdiZty3g', 'business_id': 'qjIN4UbE96Cq6JKwLIQ9VQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "This place is awesome. I'm not sure how I missed it all of these years but I'm happy to add it into my rotation of favorite places too eat. \n\nBest perk off the bat = the complimentary parking. That eliminates the stress of circling the block for a spot! \n\nNext favorite = the atmosphere is unbeatable. The decor is dark, cozy, and very Italian. There is both an upstairs & downstairs bar. The staff is friendly and very well trained. It's the perfect spot for both a nice date or a fun loud group. Try and get a seat upstairs by the live music! I didn't know this existed until we were leaving and can't wait to come back for it. \n\nJust because of the vibe of the place and how enjoyable our night was I didn't care about the food being great. But luckily each dish was fantastic!! The complimentary bread was hot and fresh and came with a delicious pesto dip. I had one of the salad specials - burrata with arugula, pear, apricots and hazelnut dressing. For my main I had the rigatoni sesso - awesome spicy sauce. My husband had the Braciole and loved it - super tender and flavorful. That comes with  cheese ravioli and OMG that was the total show stopper. I'd come back a mIllion times over for the ravioli. They were like cheesy clouds in an amazing red sauce. \n\nEveryone GO!", 'date': '2020-02-02 15:27:29', 'user': {'name': 'Courtney', 'review_count': 314, 'yelping_since': '2015-06-19 22:32:16', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.84, 'fans': 11}}
