[R42] {'review_id': 'QYedIk9hgfCDfuWMTOeUyQ', 'user_id': 'z-knoiM6Vk-TQIwfuQ6rvQ', 'business_id': 'dYinIkKBspHV5hSaukklFg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'one of the best meals we have ever eaten in philadelphia!!! we took our three boys and their significant others there for an "after christmas get-together" and boy were we pleasantly surprised!! we had 5:00 reservations and arrived at just that and were seated promptly.  we had an array of appetizers - from salad to burrata cheese to roasted vegetables and were not disappointed by any of them. they went just as fast as they came out.(what did you expect with all these boys!?!?) everyone ordered an entree; from pork milinase , spaghetti allo scoglio , lobster ravioli to braciole- and everything was fantastic!!!!  the only disappointment was we (or should i say the restaurant) did not leave any room for dessert, which all sound delicious!!  the service we received was excellent as well. we were having such a nice evening, our time got away from us and we were actually asked to leave because other people were waiting to be seated.
