[R9] {'review_id': 'wm0mEf9qfyxz8VnFYo2Odw', 'user_id': 'qsid2RnrYvGX1Ytq4LDKgg', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Had another Wonderful dinner! Meatball appetizer was yummy! Gnocchi special with shrimp in pesto sauce was perfect!!! Can't wait to return", 'date': '2020-10-19 20:51:12', 'user': {'name': 'Brenda', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2016-05-26 22:52:21', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R10] {'review_id': 'djWBprXTgJDPE8Qy7aokSQ', 'user_id': 'yzf-8f4gmJLV3nW-2RrjAg', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Wow I love this spot! In my opinion best Italian in Philly. Dined here this weekend and had such a perfect experience and unforgettable food! Service is efficient and welcoming. You can tell its a family ran place and that makes me feel at home! Come for the food...come back for the experience!', 'date': '2020-10-18 06:56:01', 'user': {'name': 'Sammie', 'review_count': 10, 'yelping_since': '2016-03-16 20:12:26', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.42, 'fans': 0}}
[R11] {'review_id': 'aRcICCwVOLWCRA2ziOJEXg', 'user_id': 'M2VBY2hxeNMhTCx2jauOJQ', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "This place is a hidden gem. A must go even if you're in philly for the day. The pasta is fresh and the sauce is tasty. The fried meatballs were good. The clams casino were really nice.  Lobster ravioli was amazing.  Shrimp scampi and risotto was really tasty and light though not what I expected as I was hoping for a more garlicky fish but it was delicious.  You will not be disappointed. It's a local favorite and byob.", 'date': '2020-09-27 04:17:53', 'user': {'name': 'Jill', 'review_count': 39, 'yelping_since': '2017-05-16 01:29:21', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.15, 'fans': 0}}
[R12] {'review_id': 'LTKrbso_kcE7YKwExIuFfQ', 'user_id': 'OPG7CM0QTzCoMyO12094BA', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Excellent from the moment I made the reservation until I paid my bill.  Very accommodating and observing all the Covid rules for outside dining.  Service was very friendly and paced very well.  The food was excellent.  My special eggplant stack appetizer was delicious as was the fried meatballs and the scungilli  diavolo.  My special salmon with the lightest tomato sauce with crabmeat was cooked to perfection.  The restaurant is a byob.  The staff surprised us with dessert and a refreshing drink when we were done.  Great evening out.  Can't wait until we can return for in restaurant dining.", 'date': '2020-08-23 22:50:03', 'user': {'name': 'A. F.', 'review_count': 4, 'yelping_since': '2013-07-28 18:28:25', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.75, 'fans': 0}}
[R13] {'review_id': 'nIh7YaJKLdBlxU7h3lbVOw', 'user_id': 'KN9iuJeZvbN66wWDCoRYDw', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "This was my family's first dining out experience after restrictions were lifted some what in Philadelphia and we could not have chose a better place! Our outside dining experience was excellent and the food was outstanding. The staff was very attentive and welcoming, they treated us like family. Large portions and great tasting food. The Gnocchi was excellent and I love there clams casino. This was our second time there and it definitely won't be our last. And also, big shot out to Lori our server who was as friendly as they come. Thank you Scannicchio's for a great time.", 'date': '2020-06-15 15:20:42', 'user': {'name': 'Rashad', 'review_count': 16, 'yelping_since': '2017-06-26 00:53:23', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.35, 'fans': 0}}
[R14] {'review_id': 'YKL_JOANTr9FbxYf8ElV0g', 'user_id': 'fv-5QhnClMVFQPVmL_39bg', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'Authentic, consistently good, and some of the best food in south Philly! I love the artichokes and the veal parm is huge!', 'date': '2020-05-01 02:25:34', 'user': {'name': 'Julie', 'review_count': 24, 'yelping_since': '2012-02-23 20:29:44', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.25, 'fans': 0}}
[R15] {'review_id': 'rqIjFr9cCVx_6CUM5USGsw', 'user_id': 'joanms0fTKN3jHyDUeMzYw', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'We ordered off the special quarantine family menu. We got chicken parm and meatballs. It came with a huge salad and bread. Everything was wrapped and sealed nicely so there were no leaks or messes when I got home. They quickly and safely handed off my food. The food itself was phenomenal!! Plenty of everything to satisfy us all.', 'date': '2020-04-25 11:29:47', 'user': {'name': 'Laura', 'review_count': 10, 'yelping_since': '2015-08-14 01:55:18', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.08, 'fans': 0}}
[R16] {'review_id': 'wEi6Bu3LxJIGaivGfsKmGQ', 'user_id': 'AJVj9G-WZu02NXJCHKAJfA', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "One of my go-to's for classic Italian food done right!  Some of my favorite dishes include the calamari Sicilian, eggplant tower, grilled romaine salad, eggplant or chicken parm, penne vodka, pumpkin ravioli, sweet potato gnocchis.  Their crab cake is my favorite -- served over sautéed spinach and vodka sauce.  I'm getting hungry just naming the things I love at Scannichios.  Some of these are specials and some are staples, but you can always ask the staff for recommendations as well!  Save room for dessert (I suggest the italian iced cream sandwich with Nutella and hazelnut gelato.).  I saw a negative review from a girl with celiac and honestly that's wild, I have a good friend w celiac and she wouldn't even consider eating at a restaurant unless they could guarantee no cross contamination of gluten (nearly impossible for an Italian restaurant that has been running since before celiac was a thing).  Soooo I guess i would say I would not recommend for celiacs or for vegans.", 'date': '2020-01-23 01:03:23', 'user': {'name': 'Candice', 'review_count': 25, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-28 04:26:02', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.63, 'fans': 0}}
[R17] {'review_id': '4eUQMf7LGCGw0WP3XHgVpw', 'user_id': 'ioNrGN-ImB-3r7E7tkqqug', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 3, 'text': 'My family & I have ate here on many different occasions, birthdays, family celebrations, etc. Great food + amazing customer service every time! Would definitely recommend!', 'date': '2020-01-22 16:33:23', 'user': {'name': 'Gi', 'review_count': 1, 'yelping_since': '2018-12-03 03:53:31', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R18] {'review_id': 't-l7phxwsE9t1vDlgBePzA', 'user_id': 'Xstf9n7v8rSOryJAuY2S7Q', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 4, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Old school Philadelphia. One of the waiters (I'm assuming he was the manager or owner) was walking around in Eagles pajamas, this was at around 9pm on a Friday night. I was here for a special event, so we had a prix fix menu, and I didn't pay, so can't comment on the price. I will say that this restaurant could be used in a movie made by Martin Scorsese if he ever does one based in Philly. It has the small, cramped, old-school, Italian, family owed vibe. The atmosphere makes you feel like you are really in Little Italy in Philly.\n\nI didn't find the food anything special. Everything tasted pretty deep fried, and didn't have that much flavor. The Chicken Parmesan was a nice size (again, tough to say if this is the regular portion size or what because it was a special event), but the flavor just tasted kinda whatever. The Penne ala Vodka just didn't have much taste; the sauce was watered down, and the pasta just was bland. Same goes with the multitude of appetizers we had, nothing really stood out in a positive way. The bread with the sauces and oils they had was pretty tasty.\n\nWhile I had an absolute wonderful time at the event, the food just wasn't for me.\n\nFood (C), Pricing (N/A), Atmosphere (B-), Service (B-)", 'date': '2020-01-04 17:47:46', 'user': {'name': 'Joshua', 'review_count': 345, 'yelping_since': '2012-12-23 08:51:04', 'elite': '2013,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.16, 'fans': 31}}
[R19] {'review_id': 'u2PGqU79mZeDoOjlqNg3GQ', 'user_id': 'M5_8DROiXkKfDaCpaUiXAw', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Had my husband's 60th Birthday and it was Fantastico!  Mike and Sandy didn't miss a beat, and the food was crazy good!  Yes we are from California and we love to go there anytime we are in Philadelphia!!!", 'date': '2020-01-03 23:55:41', 'user': {'name': 'R', 'review_count': 51, 'yelping_since': '2010-08-14 07:47:56', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.64, 'fans': 1}}
[R20] {'review_id': 'rOyi6fOvO5CdVD5fX6bw0Q', 'user_id': 'zTdqY01TtQeXEywavmE8Vg', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I absolutely loved my time here. Our waitress Kelly, was a joy with a wonderful personality. I'm amazed at how she keeps the daily specials stored in her brain! Everything was so flavorful, the atmosphere is very intimate. Perfect for date night or hanging with family. BYOB. Reservations are strongly encouraged considering the small place fills up rather quickly.", 'date': '2019-12-16 00:54:38', 'user': {'name': 'Tisheema', 'review_count': 47, 'yelping_since': '2017-07-12 00:13:59', 'elite': '20,20', 'average_stars': 3.98, 'fans': 1}}
[R21] {'review_id': 'Hfy93jfOr3SQXA8vC-xVjA', 'user_id': 'k4W4BRYvZemxKJHEOFkCLQ', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "BYOB restaurant in South Philly. I liked my gnocchi al forno, but didn't love the stuffed artichoke we had. Food wasn't super quick to come out after we ordered, but they were pretty busy.\n\n I have to say the 3 star review is more related to our waiter than the food or rest of our experience. The women who were working told us we could put in appetizer orders right away (normal, right? Appetizers is how you start the meal, why not put those in first?). But the waiter (Mark?) was adamant that entres and appetizers had to be in at the same time. Ultimately that negatively affects the restaurant because we ordered less food... \n\nOverall, an OK experience. Not amazing, not terrible, just OK.", 'date': '2019-12-12 17:52:45', 'user': {'name': 'Anna', 'review_count': 261, 'yelping_since': '2012-08-25 21:23:13', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.85, 'fans': 23}}
[R22] {'review_id': 'MDDTnYD_URTp0zEYavF4Lw', 'user_id': 'tQ8N3-j2Ckc_6ajPRg01tw', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "After many years of passing by, we finally tried this place! It was delicious and we will definitely go back.\n\nThe restaurant has an adorable ambience and the service was great.\n\nNot many places in my neighborhood are open on Monday, so it was nice to be able to go.\n\nWe ordered the eggplant caprese appetizer, Caesar salad, veal chop special, and the veal piccata. Everything was fantastic! The Caesar salad was the only dish I wouldn't get again. It was still good, but I would try a different salad. \n\nThe service was wonderful and we will definitely go back!", 'date': '2019-12-09 16:30:16', 'user': {'name': 'Rebecca', 'review_count': 106, 'yelping_since': '2015-08-29 22:08:03', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.94, 'fans': 10}}
[R23] {'review_id': 'GwZfggqYjehA3M9RbyeHZw', 'user_id': 'tD6EHQlNQV2ZN_TU_UJ2vw', 'business_id': 'uKAbrDSJJzZliY1Yqu5KxQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Words cannot describe how good this is. By far my favorite place in south Philly. They treat you like family and each every dish is thoughtfully prepared. \nTell em the "other cousin Vinny" sent you!', 'date': '2019-12-08 04:00:06', 'user': {'name': 'Brett', 'review_count': 36, 'yelping_since': '2014-04-12 15:34:12', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.59, 'fans': 0}}
