[R34] {'review_id': 'VSFl2DJBy8JoFeaMXq1QPQ', 'user_id': 'cJRdN20Qq3jlHXyTl3P03A', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Great little place to grab a fast bite highly recommended if you are in Center city...', 'date': '2018-10-25 22:50:57', 'user': {'name': 'Charles', 'review_count': 36, 'yelping_since': '2015-03-21 23:12:40', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.0, 'fans': 1}}
[R35] {'review_id': 'W58fuRX8lqEHEpRkdvJPvQ', 'user_id': 'Ttn1RtATzZBtWsx6MoPGqQ', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "What a great find! About a dozen beers on tap, a really nice variety. I usually have a hard time choosing, so many are appealing. Then the pizza - I'm a serious pizza guy, I'll drive hundreds of miles out of my way to go to New Haven, and the pizzas here are truly excellent. They really get the concept and don't try to over do it. Espresso machine to boot. New Haven, get jealous. My only warning to people who are not attentive to the menu is that the marinara pizza is indeed spicy (some people will probably find it too hot, and probably none of those people will wander in here). At the same time, my marinara pizza had fabulous basil flavor from the fresh basil leaves. Sometimes, it's worth just going with the Trenton Pie on the happy hour menu. Simple, and totally delicious. After many visits, I've developed some favorites on the menu. Specials are often worth checking out, including the Bistro Salad, which I order regularly. Always good. Recently, we tried the Cacio e pepe, which was good, although the cheese sauce on it was a bit in the direction of a more traditional mac 'n' cheese - just mentioning that in case you're looking for a more authentic Italian version. Still, quite satisfying.

And I haven't even mentioned the friendly staff. Apparently only really nice people are allowed to work here. After many visits, I'm still a fan.  Another recommendation is the Arugula Pizza, as something a little more unusual. And look for their Tiramisu. I'm not sure it's on the menu, but it is simply the best I've ever had.", 'date': '2018-10-11 17:09:33', 'user': {'name': 'David', 'review_count': 359, 'yelping_since': '2011-11-11 00:16:00', 'elite': '2015,2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.49, 'fans': 20}}
[R36] {'review_id': 'p8Aaxs00ztbr53wUuKFFDA', 'user_id': 'uXznbrfW2o2WumkfHkuCkg', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Wow. If you aren't impressed with the cool decor and fast service, then the pizza will blow u away.
So its Roman style, which means thin crust extreme.

We did 2 pizzas for 2 people, and it was a lot.  Each is a culinary explosion of flavors and textures. 

The truffle pizza, wow, and it has, wait for it...eggs on it

Great draft selection, and not too shabby on the wine selection either.", 'date': '2018-09-30 17:39:12', 'user': {'name': 'Christopher', 'review_count': 70, 'yelping_since': '2014-10-21 23:51:13', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.65, 'fans': 2}}
[R37] {'review_id': 'n5VudA7IWEOrm1YmXWVkWg', 'user_id': 'rMgHovIE-cu9qOdhMuF6HQ', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We found ourselves roaming the streets, starving and completely reservation-less on a saturday evening. Tried a couple of nearby spots , but Nomad didn't look too crowded so figured it was worth a try.
The hostess told us that they were about to have a bunch of people that actually made reservations arrive, but that she could squeeze us in toward the back of the restaurant near the kitchen. It sounded like being banished to the dungeon, but it was actually cool to be right next to the pizza making area, and see the pizza oven itself.
We were so lucky to have stumbled upon this place (thanks to yelp). It was an agonizing choice to settle on food, but we went with the seasonal veggies and arancini as apps and shared a spicy sausage pizza.
The veggies were kind of fried tempura style, but browner and crunchier...they tasted great as did the arancini which were nicely covered in think prosciutto and served with a garden fresh tomato dipping sauce.
The pizza was a hit..the sausage was spicy but not overwhelmingly and the crust had a crisp edge and simple but pleasant flavor profile. The 2 of us were barely able to finish it.
The only fail, was the moscow mule I ordered...so gross. I dont' think they put any ginger beer in it? I was close to sending it back it was that bad.
The drink aside, I would absolutely come back here again, but make a reservation.", 'date': '2018-09-17 12:45:27', 'user': {'name': 'Troy', 'review_count': 379, 'yelping_since': '2009-02-02 18:32:08', 'elite': '2015,2016,2017,2018,2019', 'average_stars': 3.68, 'fans': 33}}
[R38] {'review_id': 'Dwd_aB521ztOH6ddnjLemA', 'user_id': '3oIt2taGHPYczKYm4lISTA', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'A surprisingly good pizza place tucked away in center city. All the pizzas here are roman-style (basically really thin and crunchy crust). One pie per person is usually sufficient. 

I tried both the spicy soppressata and spicy sausage. Neither was actually spicy, but both were delicious! The spicy sausage pizza approximates a classic fennel sausage pizza in appearance and taste, but the spicy soppressata had a nice twist by throwing on some honey, which gave some sweetness to balance the saltiness of the salami.

In general, found it hard to get good pizza in philly, but this is definitely one place to try out', 'date': '2018-09-10 20:52:56', 'user': {'name': 'Matt', 'review_count': 284, 'yelping_since': '2017-01-01 20:52:39', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019', 'average_stars': 4.05, 'fans': 26}}
