[R41] {'review_id': '_1n9OYQGcJ52cT4i4yVNlw', 'user_id': 'AMazgnwFbGlDmViAQwiv-w', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Really tasty/fresh thin crust pizza!! The only reason I took a star away is because the appetizer was supposed to be grilled mushrooms and cauliflower but came out bland and soggy. They also served their house wine bottle in a carafe despite having a carafe as a lower priced item that they apparently just fill less? nonetheless a nice spot and will probably be back or will at least order takeout.', 'date': '2018-09-02 04:23:38', 'user': {'name': 'Haley', 'review_count': 25, 'yelping_since': '2018-09-02 03:48:29', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.08, 'fans': 4}}
[R42] {'review_id': 'ee6sKna7W-PSgfv_0vdr-g', 'user_id': 'dxEU4v4fSX9aD3tH8dy7cw', 'business_id': 'pxmBh8YZ6HLGQfNHvJoHzA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Really good pizza if you like extra thin crispy crust! 

I have been to nomad more times than I can probably count, and it is a really good option when looking for pizza in the center city area. The place is relatively small, but I have never had to wait for a table. My standard order is the spicy sausage pizza, which is not too spicy and has delicious crumbles of sausage and onion. I have been to the other Nomad location, and it seems that they put more toppings on their pizza (in my experience- I also only went there once) than this location, but I like this locations meatball appetizer better. I wouldn't say I crave their pizza, but my boyfriend and I really like their meatball appetizer. It comes with 3 meatballs covered with sauce and some Parmesan cheese and served with crispy bread thins and broccoli rabe. It's my fav about nomad.

My biggest issue is the service which almost makes me want to give it 3 stars. I have had multiple issues with food coming out slowly or servers just not being aware of things like empty glasses of water or coming to check in with the table. One time it was so bad that the person making pizzas in the back went up to the front to find out where our waiter was. I wish they would improve the training of staff, it would make the experience more enjoyable!", 'date': '2018-08-28 00:45:50', 'user': {'name': 'Lauren', 'review_count': 69, 'yelping_since': '2015-07-20 14:54:17', 'elite': '2018,2019', 'average_stars': 3.46, 'fans': 4}}
