[R47] {'review_id': 'wxXlv2dHXEukJFoeO6p-lA', 'user_id': 'fUqviptMEHEzGr0flP3dKA', 'business_id': 'lKU_kljhbEQKIPaM1Zbqiw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Came here on a weeknight around 9pm and was able to dine inside immediately with no reservation required. They seemed to be able to take guests but a few did show up after with reservations. Nice interior dining with glass (I believe?) dividers between every table which is a nice touch during the next phase of the pandemic. My on-again off-again partner and I had the panzanella as an appetizer. It's basically croutons, peaches, veggies, and leaves. I personally didn't think it was anything special and looked like something I could make by throwing a couple ingredients around. I prefer more complex food with different textures but I did like the honey roasted peaches. I could barely taste the extremely thin sheets of parmesan. \n\nWe ended up sharing the Campanelle Nero which is squid ink pasta with shrimp and breadcrumbs. I thought this was very tasty and was happy with the flavors combined with the crunch from the breadcrumbs. My partner and I thought it was enough for the two of us that night but if you're really hungry I could imagine it's possible to eat the whole thing yourself. I would probably recommend this dish to anyone coming for the first time. \n\nI should also add the waitress brought 2 plates out before bringing out each course which was nice and made it easy to share. She also replaced all silverware after each course so there was no peach residue in my squid ink. She came around a good amount and seemed thoughtful which I appreciate. \n\nFor dessert we had the tiramisu which was delicious as well. Another item I would recommend. \n\nAll in all, a good experience which I didn't expect that night since I'm a tough critic. Try it out!", 'date': '2021-08-08 09:38:17', 'user': {'name': 'Kevin', 'review_count': 27, 'yelping_since': '2014-12-21 23:02:03', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.33, 'fans': 0}}
