[R1] {'review_id': 'u-VpW-gbKxCZAioq5adsVg', 'user_id': 'w_rQ5XGjRkRs4KXUY0BjIg', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I had an order from here twice. The first time I was being a little fat and got 12. I like to order things in sets of twos (OCD much)? No, but I have a sister and daughter so they can try one and I try the other. We're they good? Hell yea! The second time my friend dropped me off 4 donuts because what are friends for? ! I don't know I think this might be my new spot even though I'm a certified Krispy Kreme girl.", 'date': '2022-01-15 02:45:23', 'user': {'name': 'Cynthia', 'review_count': 74, 'yelping_since': '2019-07-03 22:42:32', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.46, 'fans': 13}}
[R2] {'review_id': 'NsAVGy6yO7p16LX8k67mkg', 'user_id': 'n3u9tSWz1FZbrIU8waahnQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Good donuts! Many flavors to choose and all have their own distinct taste. I prefer the glazed cake donuts. They have a soft cake like consistency and are basically old fashion donuts with glaze on top. They are very dense. The Blueberry Fritters and Lemon Creme are a must try. So delicious, full of blueberries and lemon flavors. Donuts are also very affordable at $15.25 for a dozen and $8.00 for a half dozen.', 'date': '2021-12-24 17:15:01', 'user': {'name': 'Samira', 'review_count': 29, 'yelping_since': '2016-06-30 21:14:46', 'elite': '2021', 'average_stars': 3.93, 'fans': 0}}
[R3] {'review_id': 'w93187x2h6_5JlKXsfheVw', 'user_id': 'JSWgAb42JlHuQ1htOa3Q5g', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Fresh and delicious, although you have a plethora of options, pick up a filled donut (preferably a citrus flavor)', 'date': '2021-11-23 19:50:48', 'user': {'name': 'Jacob', 'review_count': 46, 'yelping_since': '2016-08-01 22:32:46', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.4, 'fans': 0}}
[R4] {'review_id': 'u8AvCmwjJYW84Y3tOQChNQ', 'user_id': 'hv-GtL9hsBqz8oM4vteGiQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': "Did you even go to Philly if you didn't stop at Beilers for the doughnuts. They have endless number of options to pick from that it can be overwhelming sometimes. Personal favorite are the White chocolate MnM and Fruity Pebble doughnuts. If you have a favorite, definitely recommend getting the big birthday doughnut but you have to order in advance.", 'date': '2021-10-23 14:38:37', 'user': {'name': 'Prabh', 'review_count': 69, 'yelping_since': '2018-03-18 22:17:56', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.39, 'fans': 2}}
[R5] {'review_id': '2xcGFn0J1hKMBPNVwJAjQQ', 'user_id': 'vPKSfygJwTlH6PRw-hiiGw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I went to the Beiler's Donuts in Reading Terminal and got a dozen donuts. They have a huge variety of doughnuts, and I had the Blueberry Fritter, Caramel Apple, and the French Crueller. They were pretty standard doughnuts that were sweet, with nothing negative to say about them, so my impression is that they are very popular for the variety of doughnuts they offer.", 'date': '2021-10-17 00:09:25', 'user': {'name': 'Paul', 'review_count': 16, 'yelping_since': '2021-08-28 01:16:06', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.81, 'fans': 0}}
[R6] {'review_id': 'meVUMpbXptdjMTv8NxATyQ', 'user_id': 't_O7iyu3Ceqp43hX625qWg', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Best donuts in Phildelphia. Always stop at Beiler's when we are in town. The fritters are my favorite but everything is good.", 'date': '2021-10-09 00:34:31', 'user': {'name': 'Jing', 'review_count': 673, 'yelping_since': '2013-01-16 22:17:31', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.09, 'fans': 14}}
[R7] {'review_id': 'w0PRAN9I-Euotof8Y0172Q', 'user_id': 'TEZIu1f63cV7oG7IjCHcFA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "On Saturday, 9/25 we stopped by to pick up a large chocolate cream pie to take up to college to celebrate our daughter's 20th bday.  This pie is her favorite so we made sure to take extra care to make sure it was cold and intact despite our 4 hour ride.  Unfortunately when we went to take a bite, after singing happy birthday, the cream was curdled and the pie rancid.  We were shocked & so disgusted each of us 5 had to spit it out!  Luckily my daughter has a sense of humor bec this mom felt terrible about it.  So disappointing!", 'date': '2021-09-30 13:40:33', 'user': {'name': 'Angela', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2016-06-01 13:57:42', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.6, 'fans': 0}}
[R8] {'review_id': 'Iy4AV_w7jNEHSaQwljswGQ', 'user_id': 'FdSf0UTKtDmQ8iF6C31ZRA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Quick & efficient with getting people in & out. Aesthetically delicious. The perfect sweet tooth craving fix.', 'date': '2021-08-20 17:10:09', 'user': {'name': 'Krzysztof', 'review_count': 29, 'yelping_since': '2021-03-27 20:56:59', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.1, 'fans': 0}}
[R9] {'review_id': 'vrTBYfb7QKCaXVagRvUdsw', 'user_id': 'MO-RoMKSXdbZoFVYFZDekQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'So good, I forgot to take picture up until I only had a bite left. Staff was extremely friendly and the line was long but it moved quickly. Once again, one of the best donuts I ever had', 'date': '2021-08-13 21:48:48', 'user': {'name': 'Kyle', 'review_count': 6, 'yelping_since': '2016-08-09 00:07:39', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.57, 'fans': 0}}
[R10] {'review_id': '4KEnuao4hN98OteCxMUWpQ', 'user_id': 'w5j7oPafp0kCjPuzvY_9Pw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Some of the best quality and most creative donuts you'll ever have. Nice shop in the University City area with some limited indoor seating. A must visit when in Philly.", 'date': '2021-08-11 23:58:53', 'user': {'name': 'Craig', 'review_count': 33, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-12 03:57:45', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.39, 'fans': 0}}
[R11] {'review_id': 'mXXJfXWhSR6eGvRy60Z8DA', 'user_id': 'MuQhiK9Z7xIymRRcxJMojQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 12, 'funny': 4, 'cool': 10, 'text': 'I had read and heard so much about Beiler\'s Donuts, that I had to stop in when I was in the area.  I came in expecting long lines, but I was fortunate enough to be the only one in the shop on a Friday mid-morning.\n\nI ordered a half dozen donuts to take to a friend over at Presbyterian Hospital.  Her family unanimously claimed them to be the "best donuts in Philly."  That might have been influenced by the fact that I told them Beiler\'s is credited to be the "best donuts in Philly" when I gifted them the box.  \n\nAfter my visit to the hospital, I picked up a Chocolate Iced for myself and a Sea-salt Caramel for my husband.  I have to admit, the donuts are pretty darn good. \n\nDonut Pricing: $1.50 each, $8 Half Dozen, $15.25 Dozen', 'date': '2021-08-09 15:19:08', 'user': {'name': 'Leena', 'review_count': 693, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-09 22:32:29', 'elite': '2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.81, 'fans': 130}}
[R12] {'review_id': 'dgAQt8o9eZRNu09V1A2s2Q', 'user_id': 'xZpY8ZswuOp8840V1sjxIg', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Best Donuts I have ever had - especially the Blueberry Fritter. They have so many delicious options. And the staff is super friendly.', 'date': '2021-07-16 15:06:10', 'user': {'name': 'Lauren', 'review_count': 1, 'yelping_since': '2020-03-25 17:42:18', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R13] {'review_id': 'bi5ELbFsWi1OoVbWFLVsTg', 'user_id': 'humVDS0tqNOvC-OSO764RA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I ordered the peanut butter s'mores donut. It had a white marshmallow filling, topped with chocolate, crushed graham crackers, and a s'more. The peanut butter flavor was minimal, almost nonexistent. The donut was soft and fresh, but not melt in your mouth. I would probably try something else if I go back, but this is a perfect donut for you if you love marshmallows. \n\nThe service was fast and friendly. The line takes quite a while to move due to people trying to decide which donuts they will be ordering.", 'date': '2021-07-12 15:37:35', 'user': {'name': 'Trevor', 'review_count': 264, 'yelping_since': '2017-01-20 23:13:27', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.99, 'fans': 3}}
[R14] {'review_id': 'KhWCa9i8L9oKntCJ2IkorQ', 'user_id': 'GCwPDVnQFg6DdS8KriTHNA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Better than the original location (if that's possible) - I came here on Friday afternoon right when they were closing, having called in to ask them to save a few of the original donuts for me.  Not only did they honor the request, but the staff was polite and highly professional as well.  They were friendly and knowledgeable about the offerings, and got me trying a new donut as well, something I had not done previously. \n\nThe premises were clean and well-maintained, and unlike the original location, there's designated seating that's well-maintained too. \n\nThey also have coffee!\n\nGreat customer service - they drew a smiley face on my box too!!  Will be back!", 'date': '2021-06-25 22:00:43', 'user': {'name': 'Cal', 'review_count': 138, 'yelping_since': '2008-08-11 21:20:26', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.86, 'fans': 14}}
[R15] {'review_id': 'JjmTPU_tYBgkjxnMjbfTHA', 'user_id': 'EfdJfCzZrvUI9v-bI0gv2w', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Always a delicious treat and better than other places with a reputation for fancy donuts (looking at you federal) but much better than the others and significantly cheaper. Example, average donuts last weekend from federal was $27, these amazing donuts from Beilers, $15\n\nDon't sleep on their classics either like cream filled, glazed, and apple filled. All amazing", 'date': '2021-06-05 17:04:08', 'user': {'name': 'Francesco', 'review_count': 222, 'yelping_since': '2012-09-03 01:27:43', 'elite': '2015,2016,2017,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.99, 'fans': 12}}
[R16] {'review_id': 'LV6SZelHkV9_tlYCcPQgJA', 'user_id': '9t62MB9nIqXJmAXiExmiEg', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Good for people who: want a variety of tasty doughnuts to binge eat when you're stressed from school \nBad for people who: are worried about their sugar intake \n\nAs far as doughnuts go, Beiler's is pretty good. They have a ton of good flavors and it seems like theres always a new flavor that you haven't gotten around to trying yet. The staff were really nice when I went to go pick up my nuts. I got half a dozen for my friends and I to share and we had a lot of fun trying to cut open the nuts as if they were egg yolks on top of toast or something (as you can see from the videos it's definitely not as dramatic as cutting into a yolk). My favorite is the fruity pebbles chocolate doughnut. While I'm still a federal donuts girl at heart, I'm down for Beiler's anytime.", 'date': '2021-05-30 18:04:25', 'user': {'name': 'Megumi', 'review_count': 33, 'yelping_since': '2021-05-29 21:46:50', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.18, 'fans': 6}}
[R17] {'review_id': 'JQz_F3TF3iFOAbhG6W0-Kg', 'user_id': 'k5iA70JBHhY8ucLXGR0npA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I was too close not to stop! Beiler's is a staple in Philly and a must try if your near by. I grabbed a half dozen before heading out of the city. They were totally worth the 20 minute detour and the $12 parking. The strawberry shortcake was my favorite", 'date': '2021-05-22 02:32:31', 'user': {'name': 'Carla', 'review_count': 145, 'yelping_since': '2016-07-21 10:24:58', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.49, 'fans': 13}}
[R18] {'review_id': 'y7yk5XZLBP-JsVjYflvZEg', 'user_id': 'PvRv4AGT6ySfpnnvu185oA', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "wanted to try federal donuts but they were closed due to covid hours so we ended up stopping in beiler's donuts.\n\n* the staff: kind, helpful, patient\n\n* dining area: jan. 2020 there wasn't any indoor dining so we just picked up some donuts to take home\n\n* what i ordered:\n- a dozen donuts (can't remember which ones we got exactly) - these donuts were thick and airy, not dry or hard at all! we were so happy that this impulsive stop for donuts was so delicious.\n\nsummary: 10/10 highly recommend. i guarantee you will find something here that you'll like. make sure to get there early so that they don't sell out of the flavors you want!", 'date': '2021-04-15 23:50:42', 'user': {'name': 'Samantha', 'review_count': 91, 'yelping_since': '2017-02-04 04:56:00', 'elite': '2021', 'average_stars': 4.57, 'fans': 3}}
[R19] {'review_id': '15aX7aVJmG6Xn8TM83vdJg', 'user_id': 'aYDw3rksJk9ued8V4hslTQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Melt-in-your-mouth donuts! The line of people waiting to buy the donuts says it all. These donuts are awesome!\n\nLoaded with all the goodness....butter cream sugar, so don't count calories when you are here! Because you will not know how many of them you inhaled in 2 mins!\n\nWe tried apply fritter, mocha, pumpkin spice, apply cider, oreo cream, red velvet and maple glaze. My fav (because I am  not a fan of cream filled donuts) was apple cider. Mocha was equally yummy.\n\nIf in this Philly area, Reading Terminal Market is a must try. And don't leave the market before you treat yourself with a donut from here!", 'date': '2021-04-02 18:38:40', 'user': {'name': 'Suchi', 'review_count': 36, 'yelping_since': '2011-09-27 18:04:22', 'elite': '2021', 'average_stars': 4.11, 'fans': 0}}
[R20] {'review_id': '-XnI1GFUUr39FAKYRRv5Mg', 'user_id': 'bf25MHKrD-iy--Ko7iog2g', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I have had Beiler's for the last 5 years and is one of my top donut shops. The best part is the texture of the donuts - it's chewy but airy and not cakey/dense. And the flavors are delicious and decadent. And for the price point it is amazing for about 1 dollar a donut it's better quality and price then the NYC Donuts I have tried. \n\nFavorites: my friends love the apple/blueberry fritters, I like the salted caramel, maple cream, and strawberry cake", 'date': '2021-03-11 04:16:34', 'user': {'name': 'Jennifer', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2015-12-11 02:11:16', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R21] {'review_id': 'I-sp2zlc6bplWO4mMThk6g', 'user_id': 'WntBNXWkOKP-Wqw7oPrP4A', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I ordered a dozen doughnuts for delivery about 10 minutes before they closed up for the day. Unfortunately you all had run out of a few of the donuts I asked for. Instead you sent an assortment of 2 dozen doughnuts! Very much appreciated, and we still got our favorite doughnuts in the assortment. Everything was delicious.', 'date': '2021-02-13 22:37:15', 'user': {'name': 'Paul', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2017-07-21 23:15:04', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R22] {'review_id': 'Q1c8o1rRVRSt1B3I9NE12Q', 'user_id': 'eH1Rmb5sytONhhHGGcvhdw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'There are some many varieties donuts!  And I do like many of them!  Chocolate moose, nutella, pumpkin spice (seasonal), triple chocolate, and so on!  Worth to try and very good service!', 'date': '2021-01-11 21:00:38', 'user': {'name': 'Vigrinia', 'review_count': 64, 'yelping_since': '2011-08-03 14:27:06', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.27, 'fans': 0}}
[R23] {'review_id': 'rccwzlF5nI-Oj9JCq_okOQ', 'user_id': 'lK6vU1_UCK1owB6VEIOZPQ', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Heard these were some of the best donuts in the city so had to check them out. They offer of variety and specialty donuts. They are the best, no doubt. You'll find glazed donuts and the usual favorites. Then you'll find the non-usual type of donuts, like M&M donuts, Fruity Pebbles donuts and so much more. Fresh batches made daily and often. You'll smell them once you enter Reading Terminal. Get yourself some sugary sweet treats!", 'date': '2020-12-23 18:25:02', 'user': {'name': 'Kevin', 'review_count': 564, 'yelping_since': '2011-06-16 21:42:41', 'elite': '2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.86, 'fans': 24}}
[R24] {'review_id': 'jOZP2tJ0lIM6mfrVqma_TQ', 'user_id': 'Nro6ABevZFu-8TFDKS-5bw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "$12.99 for a dozen high quality donuts?? Yes please!\n\nDonuts are thick and fluffy--the perfect texture. It gives a good bite but also melts in your mouth. They have a variety of different donuts, from the classics like glazed and chocolate sprinkled to the seasonal ones like peppermint bark to my favorites like the apple fritters. There are so many choices that it can make anyone have a favorite to choose from. I loved the fall flavors, like pumpkin pie and harvest apple. However, the caramel apple was the best. The filling was like apple pie filling, so it was so moist. I am also a fan of the Nutella and Oreo, however, the filling is the white cream. I wish there was Nutella filling or a cookies and cream filling. The PB and J donut is also really good. I like the contrast between the PB creme and the fresh jam. I wasn't the biggest fan of the cereal donuts, however. The cereal, like fruity pebbles and lucky charms, would not retain the crunch on the donut. The lemon donut was also decent, but too sour for my liking. Overall, it's definitely a good place to get some fancy donuts for a good price!", 'date': '2020-12-12 23:32:29', 'user': {'name': 'Wendy', 'review_count': 115, 'yelping_since': '2018-10-02 06:44:19', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.57, 'fans': 17}}
[R25] {'review_id': 'KwQQgvSK1cIiOV3jny249A', 'user_id': 'ET8n-r7glWYqZhuR6GcdNw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 13, 'funny': 3, 'cool': 12, 'text': "This review is going to be short and sweet because it's all about donuts and basically everyone knows that Beiler's has some of the best around. Personally, I like to keep it simple with my sweets. So I'm partial to the chocolate-frosted, cream-filled donuts or basic glazed/frosted. If you do like different flavors and toppings, there's definitely plenty of those to choose from as well. \n\nThe donuts are perfectly sized so you can enjoy one for breakfast without feeling like you blasted through half a day's calories. An excellent treat for these trying times!", 'date': '2020-11-05 21:19:58', 'user': {'name': 'Michelle', 'review_count': 2256, 'yelping_since': '2008-03-28 13:26:38', 'elite': '2008,2009,2010,2011,2012,2013,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.05, 'fans': 1353}}
[R26] {'review_id': 'LGWbgM4hr3Pk1xplAc0T9Q', 'user_id': 'EfaKpTAlu-C2HJUK4A1mOw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Antoine was super friendly and knowledgeable. He provided a great customer experience. Loved this cute place and the Nutella donut!', 'date': '2020-10-30 20:35:56', 'user': {'name': 'Rupa', 'review_count': 14, 'yelping_since': '2012-04-29 21:13:54', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.36, 'fans': 0}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'qUIGJh6t2hREkjzH9oFkiQ', 'user_id': 'fu7wU5WrMxqwYUN7mvyCUw', 'business_id': 'CQgupIpIbkyiVLUEcMIRCA', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "this review is for the 39th street location. I'm closer to the reading terminal market but with the covid, it's a little too crowded there with locals and tourists for my taste. Even before the corona, it was always too crowded. I motored over and parked which wasn't too hard because school isn't back in full swing because of the virus. Beautiful store with high ceilings and a welcoming vibe. I got the powdered vanilla creme donut. Very tasty. The counter person suggested the fritter next time which I saw another customer ask for two of and read in other reviews. I'd go back.", 'date': '2020-09-26 14:32:19', 'user': {'name': 'Glen', 'review_count': 132, 'yelping_since': '2010-07-11 08:57:38', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.69, 'fans': 4}}
