[R25] {'review_id': '0T3Oa6WDOEQuGY7NzHUfzw', 'user_id': 'EpkCj-k8O40iswbl73VNog', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Rione is seriously delicious!  The crust is probably my favorite i've had for pizza.  I will say the salads are SUPER underrated.  This arugula salad is so simple and done so right.  The parm is sharp, the pine nuts are always good and the dressing is the perfect amount of sweetness.  I am obsessed", 'date': '2020-03-04 12:56:21', 'user': {'name': 'Jenna', 'review_count': 15, 'yelping_since': '2016-05-27 20:50:38', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.81, 'fans': 0}}
[R26] {'review_id': 'wphBTZBpVYPqtg-4tUx-Og', 'user_id': 'BJYnLAu8SkwfiDogbADBtA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Can't believe I haven't reviewed this place yet! I've been here a couple times now and I have to say that their pizza might be up there with the best in the city, especially as far as slice shops go.\n\nSo the types of pizza at this joint are roman style, so they are square and almost reminiscent of the thick, sicilian style pizza that you can get in some places in new york but still has a lighter feel to it (it won't leave you feeling heavy afterwards). In fact, I would say for a solid meal, one person should probably have 2-3 slices, 4 if you are hungry. \n\nI think that what really stands out about these slices is the dough, which stands alone in terms of its own flavor - savory, chewy, and a little bit salty, just as a good dough should be. I've tried my way around many, if not most of the flavors at this point and I think that my favorites are the margherita, vodka, and whichever ones have potato on them! (The latter of those I feel like is always underappreciated). A special shout-out also has to go to their sausage slice since I thought that the sausage was super aromatic and flavorful as well.\n\nThe interior is fast-casual, yet modern and definitely not too intimidating. It is a good vibe for a fast meal alone as well as a good place to catch up with friends as well! I believe they're also BYOB so if you're looking for that kind of an experience it would work as well. Definitely check this place out.", 'date': '2020-01-26 23:32:55', 'user': {'name': 'Sam', 'review_count': 119, 'yelping_since': '2016-12-26 02:43:41', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20', 'average_stars': 4.5, 'fans': 10}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'RcssSg1wghi4G8z0vLBA6w', 'user_id': 'CKibseGOBqI7MZ2jgVu-IQ', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This place is awesome. Full selection of delicious pizza al taglio, with vegetarian and meat options. Prices are very reasonable. BYOB too! Be sure to try the great tiramisu and cannoli! The staff is super friendly. This is the place!', 'date': '2020-01-18 01:09:34', 'user': {'name': 'Paul', 'review_count': 33, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-10 19:02:39', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.66, 'fans': 1}}
[R28] {'review_id': 'hLZcYbEJjL7xM3hlo5ThKQ', 'user_id': '1msVg_B-Ef6K814sQDOTPA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "There are a lot of places you can get Roman style pizza in Philadelphia, but Rione is one of the best! 2 slices for $3.50 (which differs from my go-to pizza place Alice which is $0.60-0.70/oz). Compared to other establishments, this quaint little shop in the 20th street area of Center City excels with its fluffy pizza crust and variety of selections. \n\nWe had the Diavola which had hot soppressata (which is pork FYI!) tomato and mozzarella and a special with Alfredo sauce and potatoes. Both delicious but the soppressata is always a little drier than white sauce pizzas - as they usually are.\n\nThough on the pricier side, they do accept payments on the Ritual app which I'd highly recommend to use for deals and credits. Will be coming back the next time I'm in the neighborhood and craving good pizza.", 'date': '2019-12-23 03:25:39', 'user': {'name': 'Leslie', 'review_count': 285, 'yelping_since': '2014-11-26 23:29:38', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.95, 'fans': 26}}
[R29] {'review_id': '05FKqXeJFdqYFCj5i_JOWg', 'user_id': 'CaL1p500D0YTOTJmLArDDg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Blew my mind!! Get an assortment, all are equally phenomenal and totally unique. The crust is very light and airy with a crisp section where it meets the oven. Topping combos are nuts. No one is doing pizza like this anywhere I know of. Pizzaria Vetri is still my favorite south of New Haven but Rione has worked it's way onto my must-eats.", 'date': '2019-12-20 15:24:06', 'user': {'name': 'Andrew', 'review_count': 192, 'yelping_since': '2007-12-14 17:59:31', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.93, 'fans': 3}}
[R30] {'review_id': 'htO5eLiXWxUisUftGl34_w', 'user_id': 'VN3apynnuv00bFwNOnXqqg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "I love that we're getting more into the Roman style in Center City and I'm living for it! I opted to get the lunch special which allows you to get 3 items with option of mixing and matching (slice, suppli, half sammy, half salad), picking a margarita and another slice that I honestly can't tell you what was on it, and a suppli al telefono. I came pretty late into the afternoon just after the lunch rush, and I couldn't help but notice the timing of the pizza vs the suppli felt off. It would make more sense to drop the suppli, then toss the pizza in the over to warm back up so they finish around the same time, particularly if there's literally no other patron in the restaurant. But that's borderline picky, so I'll stop. I just had piping hot suppli and rapidly-getting-cold pizza.\n\nStill, the suppli and the pizzas were super good and I was glad I could take advantage of the reduced price. It's kind of out of the way for me but I'd definitely stop by again if I was in the neighborhood.", 'date': '2019-12-05 17:44:09', 'user': {'name': 'Jada', 'review_count': 300, 'yelping_since': '2014-09-05 04:24:48', 'elite': '2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.97, 'fans': 20}}
[R31] {'review_id': 'tYjvcEae_ZhxtTD_1xZw_Q', 'user_id': 'iJE3RnVcfHM3jsM4I6WFCw', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I walked into Rione curious about this Roman style pizza I had heard such good things about. As I walked up to the counter the entire selection of square slices of pizza looked tempting but I figured I only had room for 3 slices. I tried the margherita, the polpetta and the diavolo. The thicker than usual crust on all 3 slices was  airy but crisp on the bottom. You can hold each slice easily to eat it. The diavolo was the standout star, with its flavorful spicy soppressata making it a must on any future visit. The polpette was good, but the meatballs weren't quite as tasty as I would have liked. The margherita was exactly what you would expect, with a delicious sauce complemented with spots of cheese. The space has more seating than you would expect, making it a good spot to sit for lunch. I plan to come back for more. I'm now a Roman style pizza fan.", 'date': '2019-11-25 04:23:56', 'user': {'name': 'Ade', 'review_count': 429, 'yelping_since': '2011-04-19 20:17:24', 'elite': '2015,2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.76, 'fans': 45}}
[R32] {'review_id': 'y3VFYD3LYMbhXo_anCgzOw', 'user_id': 'KjlYa3Wlr60j-PSUZ-KfOg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'the closest you will get to roman pizza in philly. amazing stuff, very reasonably priced & BYOB. great spot to have a few beers & slices before a show at helium.', 'date': '2019-11-21 16:22:39', 'user': {'name': 'chris', 'review_count': 65, 'yelping_since': '2009-11-22 03:03:20', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.71, 'fans': 0}}
[R33] {'review_id': '6T81ehRGGj3VzQcSSAWDYA', 'user_id': '4lXwcTkAaoZoO17y9eOljQ', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 5, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 3, 'text': "Heard lots of great things about Rione. Seeing people walking past daily with Rione take out boxes got me thinking is something real good. So I decided to give it a try today since I was looking around for my lunch spot.\n\nRione is located on 21st street between Chestnut and Sansom in Rittenhouse. Many of you know stores in this area is pretty small, Rione is one of them.\n\nI order an slices of each: Patate E Salsiccia, Carciofi E. Spinaci, and Salsiccia E. Rapini. I believe these were the names but if not, plz forgive me..... I took a few bites off each of these slices bc I was starving. I didn't like all the ingredients each slice have. Kinda like it is too much weird flavor in one bite. Or maybe it is my tastebuds being off, IDK. But I couldn't eat the rest so I threw them away.\n\nReason for the 2 stars. The staff were friendly and helpful. Inside were very clean and neat.", 'date': '2019-10-28 20:32:22', 'user': {'name': 'Zhen', 'review_count': 219, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-20 19:19:07', 'elite': '2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.71, 'fans': 86}}
[R34] {'review_id': 'PmFQVBU6rAOOTAZaKO1qxg', 'user_id': 'qzvKlDLs2eE9OtHlN_yWpA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I've heard such great reviews of Rione so I ordered and was u fortunately disappointed, I'm really hoping it was just a bad night. Barry any pesto on the tricolora slice and my friend ordered the margarita and said the sauce was lacking flavor. For the price I'm not overly upset but who doesn't want a ton of pesto on the slices! I'm not sure I'll give them a second chance.", 'date': '2019-10-11 22:25:47', 'user': {'name': 'Maddy', 'review_count': 10, 'yelping_since': '2015-05-28 22:36:13', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.9, 'fans': 0}}
[R35] {'review_id': 'qnew-lL6IFmZejAZj25gpg', 'user_id': '-zFn-szI6fDgZiCHg4C4zA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "One of the best pizza places in Philly! Great late night food, but honestly good anytime of the day. The place is really simple and nice, with plenty of seating. We're vegetarian and we get plenty of options there! Haven't had a bad pizza there yet. Would definitely recommend!", 'date': '2019-09-20 18:32:07', 'user': {'name': 'Krishna', 'review_count': 11, 'yelping_since': '2018-03-06 17:08:07', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.55, 'fans': 0}}
[R36] {'review_id': 'cS-4ix-Yhi0wNqDf4MvkxA', 'user_id': 'xDQlc86OBoSPS5NgaUyFuw', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'ugh this was such a satisfying meal. bf and i   got delivery. margarita, carbonara, truffle, fra diavlo, potato & sausage, \n\nthe crust was crispy (without being at all burnt) the inside was airy and doughy. \n\ni enjoyed all of them. i ate soo much and didn\'t feel gross. not greasy at all just super yummy ! \n\nidk how i can order any other ones after trying those! i recommend trying a bunch for sure. & the tiramisu "individual" is in the perfect small individual size. soo gooodo', 'date': '2019-09-14 01:19:42', 'user': {'name': 'Jennifer', 'review_count': 32, 'yelping_since': '2013-08-30 21:53:30', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.44, 'fans': 0}}
[R37] {'review_id': '-2JxRny5itRF18WihTYnsQ', 'user_id': 'zQqfwJDt5dPPbkggyXg6wg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "My hope is that today was an off day... a very off day. Arrived around 12:10 to get some pizza as the shop has great reviews and was recommended to me by a friend. There were about 5 people in front of me in line but somehow it took close to 15 minutes for me to place my order of 4 slices of pizza. The guy at the register was very friendly. Told me about a discounted lunch special and I paid and I was very much looking forward to my pizza. But then I kept waiting....and waiting... and waiting. I don't know what was going on behind the register but all they needed to do was reheat some slices of pizza. Every order that came out before mine, aside from taking an absurd amount of time, was wrong. There was a line of about 14 people all waiting on their food or complaining because they got the wrong food. After about 40 minutes of waiting I walk out and went back to work...hungry. I can't imagine that this is a typical experience but it sure was a memorable one and not in a good way. $16 lost :-(", 'date': '2019-09-10 20:43:35', 'user': {'name': 'Nate', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2015-10-11 15:55:58', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R38] {'review_id': 'EeGNsNjK_gJvipiZPVGb2g', 'user_id': 'jX5qmRYgD2eiSfCDkoKeSg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Never any complaints. Fun folks and awesome pizza. I always grab a few extra for breakfast the next day. Variety is the spice of life so try a few diff slices!!!', 'date': '2019-09-10 15:41:49', 'user': {'name': 'S', 'review_count': 9, 'yelping_since': '2017-03-30 01:03:27', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.6, 'fans': 1}}
[R39] {'review_id': 'wN33hPWNslVEdvajyY5aSQ', 'user_id': 'DHL4qn4MPq1vtxrv4t9hAQ', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Eggplant pizza! With whole fresh basil leaves! \n\nI have nothing else left to say!  *magnifico*', 'date': '2019-08-26 00:53:59', 'user': {'name': 'Malissa', 'review_count': 4, 'yelping_since': '2018-02-04 01:28:51', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.75, 'fans': 0}}
[R40] {'review_id': 'GK023R1AXYWcicbVXHp3PA', 'user_id': 'U8NZXzQ8JJnVYc8gPj6pvg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'After going to two pizza places that were closed and one that only sold whole pies, I walked about 8 or 9 blocks and found this place and I\'m glad I did.\n\nIt\'s hard to see unless you look hard for its limited signage on the storefront, but worth looking for.\n\nI had a slice of the Marinara (aka tomato) pie and a slice of Margherita. I asked for them to be cooked to well done status to make the crust extra crispy.\n\nFirst I liked that all of the slices are sicilian (square) slices, that the staff (led by Jamaal) was very friendly and accomodating even when I  asked for extra crispy and additional sauce, and that everything came out correctly as I ordered it.\n\nNext, I liked the taste, once I added the additional sauce, hot pepper flakes and oregano.\n\nThe table area is roomy and comfortable unlike some (not all) other places I\'m used to in an urban environment, air conditioned and when I visited featured upbeat soul and rock music, helping me "get my groove on."\n\nThe menu is filled with good choices, including my favorite- cannolis, which at a small size of just 3 x 4 inches were tasty. I wish they were the normal (larger) size, as it takes 2-3 of the smaller size to get the real cannoli experience.\n\nThe prices were fair and right where I expected.\n\nMy only minor disappointment is the inability to add toppings I like  such as anchovies, pepper, onion, etc. to the already made pizza. In fairness I didn\'t ask until afterwards but Jamaal confirmed what I suspected-  the way the slices are is how they are sold, no add-ons, although they may be able to remove a topping if practical and asked to do so (best for everyone if you remove what you don\'t want)\n\nI recommend eating here. You won\'t regret it.', 'date': '2019-08-18 20:09:19', 'user': {'name': 'Jp', 'review_count': 131, 'yelping_since': '2012-12-10 23:13:14', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.04, 'fans': 2}}
[R41] {'review_id': '84FJbQUj89AhrNE8QhaWHQ', 'user_id': 'aseEvu-Lz6NUjMlSSbEGDA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This place has a nice feel. The inside is really cool, small but like a regular pizza spot.. but it isn't. \n\nThey have some nice specialty pizzas, Roman-style. Very airy and a nice variety. \n\nWe weren't huge fans of the pizza, they were ok. We got the potato one and the margarita one. Again, average, wouldn't go bonkers over it. It was nice, got the job done, but nothing special.  The rice ball on the appetizer menu was really good! Would come back for that. \n\nWas nice to check out and try, it's off the checklist but not sure if we would come back for the pizza.", 'date': '2019-08-07 03:52:40', 'user': {'name': 'Ajay', 'review_count': 73, 'yelping_since': '2014-01-03 17:37:06', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.23, 'fans': 4}}
[R42] {'review_id': 'mWYXAgmyufb2459SY5Rxbw', 'user_id': 'KL3pyH7Vx-oxROB0ViioTg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Sauce is way too over powering. Couldnt comprehend the pizza beyond the sauce. It was like having pan con tomate instead of pizza. Didnt like the base too much either, needs to be made a bit lighter probably. Tiramisu was alright. Nothing extraordinary.', 'date': '2019-07-31 22:59:48', 'user': {'name': 'Akash', 'review_count': 4, 'yelping_since': '2016-08-03 14:50:19', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.5, 'fans': 0}}
[R43] {'review_id': 'lnOkL2aSdNJpJR9HQDWB-Q', 'user_id': 'LnKOEQ0n6CFWmQMkHPvgyw', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Ordered two half sheets from here one carbonara and one regular. Came out pretty terrible to be honest. I had really high hopes for Rione especially after seeing all the great reviews. However, it just was a let down AND I paid $50! I understand it\'s "Roman style" pizza and thus square with thicker crust but the taste was incredibly bland. The sauce was bland and the cheese tasted like shredded kraft cheese melted on top. Hopefully the chef was just having an off day or something but I don\'t know....', 'date': '2019-07-27 01:31:00', 'user': {'name': 'Thomas', 'review_count': 4, 'yelping_since': '2013-02-20 14:21:02', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.25, 'fans': 0}}
[R44] {'review_id': 'hXDnYrEVVcp9CikcTFGelQ', 'user_id': 'VL2NGgDqG8CoKt7VsG2j_Q', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Rione is a good place to pick up a filling, relatively inexpensive lunch. For $9, you can pick choose any three from a variety items (including pizza slices and a 1/2 salad, because I'm not going to pretend that I know what a suppli or a crochette is). \n\nI opted for two slices (the carciofi e spinaci and the salsiccia e rapini) and 1/2 Caesar salad. The pizza was pretty good---the crust was a tad crispier than what I prefer, but the salt level was perfect and the toppings were flavorful. As for the salad, the Caesar dressing (note: all of their dressing are made in-house) was fantastic: creamy, cheesy, and potent. Special emphasis on the potent...resist the urge to dump the entire container in your salad, because I can assure you that you do not need that much.\n\nAll in all, if you need a quick cheap lunch in Rittenhouse, Rione is a solid choice.", 'date': '2019-07-21 19:54:35', 'user': {'name': 'Nonye', 'review_count': 74, 'yelping_since': '2014-04-06 16:46:37', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.09, 'fans': 13}}
[R45] {'review_id': '8gDGxmHb9-xdVum9vhb6WQ', 'user_id': 'wEN4jfGW1bYc5tfZ6c2hog', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'The pizza is bomb!! Friendly staff, flavorful food and all-gender restrooms. Stumbled in when I was walking around the neighborhood and this was the greatest accidental great dinner ever', 'date': '2019-07-18 00:17:20', 'user': {'name': 'Xochi', 'review_count': 29, 'yelping_since': '2015-06-25 13:40:35', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.61, 'fans': 0}}
[R46] {'review_id': 'L6tDHOFxj-nEZM32fc1nZQ', 'user_id': '371aOxqzw12qUV_y4sDekQ', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The pizza at rione is just amazing. The fluffy crust is so good and the toppings are always done so proportionately. The salsiccia is a personal favorite (sausage, potato, rosemary, and mozzarella) as well as the prosciutto crudo. The Suppli al Telefono Cacio E Pepe is also extremely good. When it comes to pizza, these guys know what they're doing.", 'date': '2019-06-26 20:36:26', 'user': {'name': 'Simran', 'review_count': 70, 'yelping_since': '2016-07-24 01:45:23', 'elite': '2021', 'average_stars': 4.21, 'fans': 0}}
[R47] {'review_id': 'DHVSIdOsWQj1FhYwGQnwDg', 'user_id': 'mRJ3oXyskDngWiu13khTvA', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Having sustained myself for a full year in college on pizza al taglio in Rome, I can attest that this is the real deal. The dough is just the right combination of crispy on the bottom and eccentrically pillow-y on top, which is the cornerstone of real Roman street pizza. It's delicious. Plus, they have pizza patate e rosmarino (potato and rosemary). It doesn't get more Roman than that, and it's perfect. My other favorite slices that seem like Rione's own great inventions are the trufolata and parmigiana. In short I highly recommend this place, especially if you'd like to experience a bite of Rome in Philly!", 'date': '2019-06-22 01:33:25', 'user': {'name': 'Emily', 'review_count': 3, 'yelping_since': '2017-04-24 14:06:30', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.33, 'fans': 0}}
[R48] {'review_id': 'ewshlb09vKP-FFtWZETRMw', 'user_id': 'VTv7t0ZqvA8JEcHdUrKz4g', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This pizza is so good - the crust is the right mixture of crunchy bottom and doughy top. The sauce has a great (low) level of acidity, with yummy chunks.', 'date': '2019-05-17 23:07:42', 'user': {'name': 'Nile', 'review_count': 57, 'yelping_since': '2011-09-22 00:35:13', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.76, 'fans': 1}}
[R49] {'review_id': 'qa6TF8439iPoCcCl_smlfQ', 'user_id': 'Ariwz06at3CtbWZM-gPMAg', 'business_id': 'IzyQVIJG8JAnOiRQPb0-wg', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 3, 'cool': 5, 'text': 'Let me start my review with a bit of background: I love pizza, particularly pizza by the slice (as it is offered here), and as a consulting and research scientist, I also have a very strong background in fermented foods (and fermented nutritional supplements as well). Of course, in part because of the fact that I am a scientist who works with fermented foods and nutritional supplements, I am well aware of the health benefits of eating fermented foods, and of the even far more powerful health benefits afforded by long-fermented grain products such as long-fermented pizza dough.\n\nI should also mention that I have, in the past, made batches of long-fermented sourdough bread where the dough had been fermented for 3 to 4 days before cooking the loaf. In fact, it is safe to go further and say that I am a connoisseur of long-fermented breads and other dough-based products. The flavor and texture of long-fermented dough products alone make them stand out heads and shoulders above other baked products, and the added nutritional benefits are just one more plus!\n\nI first discovered this unique and worthy shop while on a walk one morning while visiting Philadelphia a few years ago. When I walked in to check out the shop, I was stunned, and incredibly pleased, to discover that they make the dough for all of their pizza and other dough-based products only using long-fermentation methods, wherein the dough is allowed to ferment for at least 72 hours before baking! Yummy! \n\nSince that time, every time that I visit Philadelphia -- which is usually twice per year, for about 7-8 days per stay -- I always visit this shop to pick up a few slices of pizza, which I then bring back to my room, where I eat as much as I can, and then the rest goes in the fridge for later meals.\n\nThe quality of this pizza