[R16] {'review_id': 'te53x-lHaGHt_2MDn52bBQ', 'user_id': 'Dlh0viSrImf8nW_-w_9H4A', 'business_id': 'bTve2mwLk5Zc01vRKqc2KQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We were searching vegan breakfast options that were near Dottie's Donuts (vegan donuts) and came across this place. The boyfriend ordered a Vegan Elvis (peanut butter, banana, agave and vegan bacon then pan fried) and fell in love! It came with a side of vegan potato salad. Would definitely recommend to a vegan and/or non-vegan. It looked and tasted delicious (picture included for drooling purposes). \n\nI went with a toasted sesame bagel with cream cheese and bacon. Simple but delicious--I promise you. I was expecting bacon strips but it was covered in bacon bits so every bite was perfect!\n\nWe were both happy with the choice and agreed it's definitely a spot we'd come back to when in Philly. Don't hesitate, just go! You won't regret it.", 'date': '2019-12-01 02:39:45', 'user': {'name': 'Kisbel', 'review_count': 81, 'yelping_since': '2011-09-19 20:09:43', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.08, 'fans': 3}}
