[R16] {'review_id': '2zG3fmPPmi5c_1V92krBSA', 'user_id': 'TFvhSVpxUgZWks1cZqpakA', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 3, 'text': "This place KNOCKS MY SOCKS OFF.\n\nYou walk by and at first glance it may seem like any other city market/deli - average selection and overpriced. IT IS NOT - I urge you to go in and check it out.\n\nFirst of all, the people here are so nice. And somehow, they have EVERYTHING. Not only are their sandwiches some of the best I've ever experienced in my life, anytime I find myself needing or craving anything - they have it. For example, a few weeks ago I was sick and wanted some ginger for my throat - called them and they not only were stocked with fresh ginger but also cough and cold medicine. My favorite Pistachio Talenti? Check. La Croix flavors I didn't even know existed? Check. Regular hot fresh brewed coffee? Check. The list goes on.\n\nThe service is soooo nice and kind and friendly. And now let me get back to the sandwiches. THE SANDWICHES ARE HEAVEN. They incorporate pesto, sun-dried tomato, and a variety of other subtle but incredible spreads and spices and they just taste better than any sandwich I've ever experienced. And they are usually $5-6 max. I come here WAYYYYY too often. \n\nLong story short - BEST MARKET EVER. I will continue to live here (3-4 times a week, no joke).", 'date': '2017-04-13 12:37:22', 'user': {'name': 'Farha', 'review_count': 131, 'yelping_since': '2011-01-31 18:34:36', 'elite': '2015,2016,2017', 'average_stars': 3.89, 'fans': 34}}
[R17] {'review_id': 'T-lKSzzd-2fm29Ua-6I5Fg', 'user_id': '27km-ZQwZMMq_Yooq3nSIw', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': 'Palm Tree has become one of my favorite places for lunch. The sandwiches are always packed with fresh cut lunch meat, fresh vegetables & bread. And the best part is they DELIVER in the neighborhood. There always super nice on the phone & delivery is quick. For $8 i get a packed sandwhich, chips & a drink delivered. I highly recommend them.', 'date': '2016-11-10 16:05:51', 'user': {'name': 'Teresa', 'review_count': 26, 'yelping_since': '2013-05-13 11:48:58', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.14, 'fans': 0}}
[R18] {'review_id': 'RMcq0GqwNWk7cWAoxRT3-Q', 'user_id': 'Gz7iVvFjxCp11FZPwm1Z5g', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Good but I wouldn't classify this as $ it's definitely $$ and some may argue $$$. People are nice. Cash under 20$ is annoying but they have a MAC machine. Yes I said MAC machine bc that's what you say in F-tizzy, it's all about that throwback.", 'date': '2016-04-13 23:45:29', 'user': {'name': 'Tom', 'review_count': 19, 'yelping_since': '2012-10-21 19:23:57', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.75, 'fans': 1}}
[R19] {'review_id': '_1lTxscSg5oMRJh6OgxJxQ', 'user_id': 'vmzxlBkQUd6VJFSewSt78A', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I love Palm Tree Market! This is more of a grocery store with a deli for carryout sandwiches. This is my go-to place for carryout sandwiches. Sandwich prices can't be beat (I love the chicken salad on a wrap, or many of their paninis). Breakfast sandwich for $2.99, YUM! This is also a great place to stop by to grab a couple potatoes or an onion etc rather than having to go to a grocery store - AND I have found their produce and fruit prices to be cheaper than Acme. What!! Occasionally they have good grocery deals - like Yogi tea, 2 for $7, or a bag of La Colombe coffee for $7.99. They have a coffee station as well if you need to grab coffee and a breakfast sandwich to go in the morning. It's a deal, and a quick shout out to the friendly guys making the delicious sandwiches - they are awesome.", 'date': '2016-04-05 16:26:08', 'user': {'name': 'Natalie', 'review_count': 11, 'yelping_since': '2015-07-13 15:12:30', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.36, 'fans': 1}}
[R20] {'review_id': 'zK7K4N5W0Nty062lTL6x9Q', 'user_id': 'so-LsUevlXOgZPe9CkBnhQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The $5 minimum for credit cards is pretty annoying, but the hoagies are pretty good and you can't beat the $3 breakfast sandwiches. Some of the stuff in the market can be a bit pricey and other stuff priced comparable to larger grocery stores. They have an interesting selection of munchies, things you don't really see in a chain store", 'date': '2016-01-22 22:12:03', 'user': {'name': 'William', 'review_count': 6, 'yelping_since': '2016-01-22 22:11:52', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.17, 'fans': 0}}
[R21] {'review_id': 'jKsGMB7rx8MK9TjWcSmrIQ', 'user_id': 'EYmOBoavA7oE0Io4e3DOqw', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Love this place. They're very friendly and they carry many high quality, organic and natural products. I also have never been disappointed with the fresh food ordered at the deli counter.\n\nThey are a little more expensive than a chain/grocery store, but I'd rather give my money to a small business in the neighborhood.", 'date': '2015-12-18 16:47:30', 'user': {'name': 'Evan', 'review_count': 11, 'yelping_since': '2015-04-02 17:54:31', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.08, 'fans': 0}}
[R22] {'review_id': 'bg8ZqgSP45tFr5JMqTv_KQ', 'user_id': 'qeWLlOFXiNz8yuQ_wQDxsg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'My life was changed today. I had the most delicious sandwich ever. Chicken hummus. I highly recommend it. I love the variety of snacks they sell as well. Try it out!', 'date': '2015-09-03 22:04:26', 'user': {'name': 'Danielle', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2014-11-23 16:07:40', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R23] {'review_id': 'RpaexkgUnW7KSihbSguofQ', 'user_id': 'jZgihdS6_xxldYg-Eo64Rw', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The best sandwiches - big, great bread, fresh ingredients, fair price. Can't beat it. Plus they have all the essentials of a grocery store if you need to pick up anything last minute.", 'date': '2015-05-31 19:21:46', 'user': {'name': 'Hannah', 'review_count': 19, 'yelping_since': '2013-04-18 02:20:23', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R24] {'review_id': 'onO2WCQ8BkpgYHWCh5knwA', 'user_id': 'USD9k93iOIB88v93B5iBcw', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Don't know what happened to this place which I used to like a lot. We stopped in for lunch and got the grilled chicken sandwich with avocado tomato and honey mustard and the grilled chicken salad. The chicken was awful. It was identical to lean cuisine chicken. Fake chicken. Awful.", 'date': '2015-05-16 20:40:47', 'user': {'name': 'Alex', 'review_count': 304, 'yelping_since': '2011-06-03 18:58:25', 'elite': '2012,2013,2014,2015,2016', 'average_stars': 4.06, 'fans': 6}}
[R25] {'review_id': 'ei68MnZ5Lsd92MKyJJHv5Q', 'user_id': 'NlmGjBri_WrYO56CkezQFQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Clean, friendly, fast. Yes, some items are overpriced, but you can't beat it for the convenience and the option to find healthy snacks. Can't go wrong!", 'date': '2015-04-07 08:01:02', 'user': {'name': 'BB', 'review_count': 14, 'yelping_since': '2014-12-19 05:52:30', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.18, 'fans': 0}}
[R26] {'review_id': 'ywwlRCpjNP1budYdj7-xJQ', 'user_id': '57PsuHGDflfLyH5Mv8SNBg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Great convenience store with early/late hours. A little pricey however that's what you'd usually expect. The deli is very reasonable with a basic egg and cheese breakfast sandwich costing $2. Can't beat that as you wait 40 mins next store at Green Eggs for $12 entrees. The store offers a wide range of gluten free options as well, including their deli which offers bohrs head meat. They recently took out table and chairs to eat as I guest they had some people from green eggs waiting inside.", 'date': '2015-03-22 21:55:57', 'user': {'name': 'Mags', 'review_count': 76, 'yelping_since': '2014-03-27 16:44:31', 'elite': '2015', 'average_stars': 3.54, 'fans': 8}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'ea-Hw_cDdLKNzxaKxVldXA', 'user_id': 'akL-jZcQZvyUcPkQEUK5wg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Awesome little market. I don't do as much grocery shopping here because some of there stuff is pricey/unqiue. But the deli/breakfast sandwiches are SO fresh and delicious and extremely inexpensive. I can get a great breakfast sandwich on a good bagel for $2.99. Then grab a cup of La Colombe to go. It's great.", 'date': '2015-02-02 20:26:43', 'user': {'name': 'Eric', 'review_count': 14, 'yelping_since': '2014-03-17 17:30:32', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.6, 'fans': 4}}
[R28] {'review_id': 'MgjcN_zw_ULh4xmHOc8yZA', 'user_id': 'NbBKe8BJtpeh1RRQSa-FXQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'Great addition to the neighborhood, with great food, would update to five stars; however, I cant get over minimums for credit card purchases in this day in age. \n\nThat said great food, nice people, and ample selection for a smaller market.', 'date': '2014-12-31 19:37:03', 'user': {'name': 'Joe', 'review_count': 98, 'yelping_since': '2012-09-20 02:06:53', 'elite': '2015,2016', 'average_stars': 4.26, 'fans': 2}}
[R29] {'review_id': 'tYebhLgfSfES9DGApQy_Qw', 'user_id': 'Bkhgg8oF70OFsfipiRXiHg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The sandwiches are good but they don't use a lot of meat kind of cheap with the ingredients. Good variety of products for a small store. The reason I am giving it two stars is because the prices are obnoxious. i'll spend $10+ buying a coffee a cookie and and apple. Everything is overpriced it pisses me off ..if they weren't so obnoxious with the prices I would rate this place four or five stars I know a lot of people that stop shopping here because of that.", 'date': '2014-12-29 01:12:43', 'user': {'name': 'Julie', 'review_count': 17, 'yelping_since': '2013-08-18 17:53:22', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 2.56, 'fans': 0}}
[R30] {'review_id': '_77lSSzmuP1eCiZjrjXzkQ', 'user_id': 'H2RalfY3Jn_GSEB4g_LOqg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Small boutique grocery store with great selection of high quality stuff.  Yes, the prices are pretty high.  Many things you can get for cheaper elsewhere.  Sometimes it's more convenient to just get them here.  I think the deli is very good.  Good hoagies and sandwiches of all sorts, including the vegan stuff.", 'date': '2014-03-09 06:47:51', 'user': {'name': 'Jonas', 'review_count': 32, 'yelping_since': '2013-05-22 01:12:17', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.24, 'fans': 1}}
[R31] {'review_id': 'vJsNEh-fszXxJE-5zbJOyA', 'user_id': '6FYZcN3ce5_ac-ooiszJUQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I don't get it with the rave about this place. I live across the street and would have every reason to laud this place for its excellence. Bottom line, its like just about every other corner store except with the prices jacked up. EVERY SINGLE sandwich I have gotten from there has been incredibly skimpy. From egg sandwiches to wraps to turkey hoagies. $7 gets you basically a roll with 3 strips of turkey and whatever else you have on it. And the egg sandwiches I literally had to open up the thing to see if there was egg on it.\n\nThe plus side, they have a lot of stuff including produce. Instead of going up to super fresh to grab veg for dinner or avocadoes, I can go here. But if it werent for the convenience I wouldnt bother.  Staff is nice, but so are great big sandwiches. That said, this area doesnt offer much in the way of neighborhood delis.", 'date': '2014-03-04 02:07:39', 'user': {'name': 'Seth', 'review_count': 14, 'yelping_since': '2011-01-13 17:05:30', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 1.93, 'fans': 1}}
[R32] {'review_id': 'Aps4GPdyjXTE8htEu2Spxg', 'user_id': 'f6xS_-hD1lZ24oWeYKnkQA', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This place is highly overated. I'm sorry, they get A for effort but that's about it. Everything in there is over priced, especially when the same products can be found relatively cheaper in the surrounding neighborhood markets. I ordered a Caesar wrap and was amazed at how small it was, more wrap than ceasar, so maybe what it lacked in size it would make up for in taste. Sad to say it didn't. All in all this place is a last resort. If you have no other options you go here. I could name plenty of places within a half mile radius that have better quality and are less expensive.", 'date': '2014-02-18 17:59:11', 'user': {'name': 'Abijah', 'review_count': 24, 'yelping_since': '2012-10-11 02:43:18', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.25, 'fans': 1}}
[R33] {'review_id': 'x0kK_WneVdgtOYi1D-izXA', 'user_id': '5vVYmqdTQNqRzvgWBXCEtA', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Great Deli. All fresh Boar's Head meats. I usually get the turkey club hoagie or corned beef Ruben. Prices for the deli are very reasonable, but everything else is pricey. Friendly staff make the sandwiches quickly every time.", 'date': '2014-01-19 04:23:11', 'user': {'name': 'Brett', 'review_count': 72, 'yelping_since': '2013-09-06 13:40:55', 'elite': '2016,2017,2018', 'average_stars': 3.88, 'fans': 6}}
[R34] {'review_id': 'gSoD76t7TviWjSgEkJtckA', 'user_id': 'f4v6QDA88r8RZAEpCsVsTQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': '#12 .. cream cheese, honey mustard, cucumber and turkey on sour dough bread. OMG\n\nthe staff here is really nice and super quick as well. two thumbs up.', 'date': '2014-01-15 22:24:34', 'user': {'name': 'Brittany', 'review_count': 592, 'yelping_since': '2011-07-03 00:03:09', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.35, 'fans': 9}}
[R35] {'review_id': 'P7vdOfYIEF_CN7sKPwindQ', 'user_id': 'H4Bmy6XBy7NDgJ7l-zaJfg', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I never write reviews but I love this place! The staff is really friendly and the food is always fresh and yummy. I work down the street so I go here at least once a week and never get tired of it. mmmm', 'date': '2013-12-21 23:10:43', 'user': {'name': 'Nadia', 'review_count': 2, 'yelping_since': '2013-12-21 18:27:49', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 5.0, 'fans': 0}}
[R36] {'review_id': '_tfviAhXVr_FsEsQA8BQVg', 'user_id': '3K6tBpPs2D4PbUAGfP863w', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "When I lived in Northern Liberties, I loved going to the spring garden Asian grocery store for my groceries. However, sometimes Palm Tree would be my destination, especially if you need something later in the night! They are open kinda late, which is awesome. \nI absolutely love their sandwiches, especially the veggie cheesesteak. It's not Govinda's, but it's still really damn good. Sometimes I would come here just for this sandwich. Also got one of their salads once and it was super fresh and no wilty-ness at all!\nTheir produce is good too, but just kind of expensive. They have a lot of veggie friendly items and just about everything you need for a tasty hearty meal", 'date': '2013-11-19 02:06:33', 'user': {'name': 'Danie', 'review_count': 528, 'yelping_since': '2009-08-03 17:26:04', 'elite': '2013,2014', 'average_stars': 3.43, 'fans': 43}}
[R37] {'review_id': '-9jPFV34ZWI-wE8bsW0r3w', 'user_id': 'Sy5vUIGlxBHEZrqdlPrLVA', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Love this place.  Great salads, sandwiches, and even sushi.  Super friendly staff.  Perfect convenient neighborhood market.', 'date': '2013-09-30 13:06:55', 'user': {'name': 'Amanda', 'review_count': 6, 'yelping_since': '2010-11-19 00:28:56', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.67, 'fans': 1}}
[R38] {'review_id': 'qjPsK4uVmtvfAoYTYcV3Qg', 'user_id': 'CY8RGnMSKfHaqZqeMImvFQ', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "The Palm Tree Market is one of those sleeper places in your neighborhood that  just make life better. \n\nThis little spot has everything you could need ... laundry soap, cat food, fresh mangoes ...\n\n... And the very best Italian Hoagie you will ever eat. Amazing bread, sharp provolone, Boar's Head cold cuts, amazing! Accompanied by a giant dill pickle, this is pretty much the ideal lunch. \n\nA good variety of salads, veggie choices, prepared foods and produce combined with great prices means that I don't go anywhere else for groceries. They also have fresh bagels and white fish spread, yummy.\n\nThe staff are super nice too. \n\nSo glad I live around the corner.", 'date': '2013-09-07 17:42:48', 'user': {'name': 'Lisfrancs', 'review_count': 49, 'yelping_since': '2007-07-09 12:11:06', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.45, 'fans': 0}}
[R39] {'review_id': 'HOtipl889a5_pn-ErNyeeg', 'user_id': '4UAqdgiCe1jwI1IQl96MIA', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I have never eaten at Palm Tree Market (I will have to change that) but I have purchased groceries from them many times and have always been happy with the selection and service.  \nIt's a small shop that carries a lot of whole, unadulterated foods, just the way I like it as it is perfect for preparing meals from scratch.  They do also have handy snacks that are ready to eat or drink.  This place is definitely worthy.", 'date': '2013-07-11 01:32:07', 'user': {'name': 'Gabriela', 'review_count': 573, 'yelping_since': '2008-12-15 22:49:53', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.47, 'fans': 26}}
[R40] {'review_id': '5HfrNtJATg_GNv-5OnLQpA', 'user_id': 'D2VBAKQjN2L5P7RxflQFMw', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Lots of 4 star reviews lately, I know.  (as if people are really following along!)  But it's hard to get inspired by a mediocre experience.  A really bad experience will get me all fired up, but it takes a lot to disturb me.  Anyway, where in the heck was I going with this??\n\nOh yes, the Palm  ...a great convenient gourmet mash-up of a place for sure.  They have a little bit of everything, in a good way.  Metropolitan bread, great salads & sandwiches, edible sushi from down the street & plenty of veggie/vegan options in the ready-made and frozen cases.  It's perfect for the Nolibbing, disposable income resident. And anyone who wants a decent lunch to be honest.", 'date': '2013-05-31 01:34:09', 'user': {'name': 'Sophia', 'review_count': 321, 'yelping_since': '2011-09-30 15:02:49', 'elite': '2013,2014,2015,2016,2017,2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.84, 'fans': 25}}
[R41] {'review_id': 'DcUvcujQO6bUtOElCf7kdQ', 'user_id': 'Oc1sUvS71H5lgelmy2dw1A', 'business_id': 'vEgKBcuZxPsaExMXBP0SgQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This place has everything.. I went there for the first time to pick up random ingredients for dinner one night on the way home from work. I walked in with wishful thinking and they ended up having everything I needed. I browsed around to see they had A LOT of awesome food, and now return quite often on my breaks from work.', 'date': '2013-05-09 18:08:06', 'user': {'name': 'Stacey', 'review_count': 7, 'yelping_since': '2009-07-20 15:22:28', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.29, 'fans': 0}}
