[R19] {'review_id': '_9ukvAtkwJINgqbt36RHNA', 'user_id': 'Al8dyLkVPJ6_-G5p7qMQxw', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'Waaawaaweewa. Quick Breakfast in the airport is sometimes hard to find but with 6 mins to boarding this place hit the spoooot. HUGE panini sandwich and pizza that could be shared with two people!! Great prices honestly for the size of the food. Conveniently located in C terminal in the middle of all the gates. Worth a try if your in the philly airport! I heard lunch is good too', 'date': '2019-08-06 12:00:51', 'user': {'name': 'Emma', 'review_count': 96, 'yelping_since': '2012-06-23 20:55:30', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.52, 'fans': 12}}
[R20] {'review_id': 'NQaDsWF3gDI_T8KY9fHJcA', 'user_id': 'bHiU4fPgjPGzvBCl5BYOVA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "An unexpected gem. You don't expect to find some of the best pizza you'll ever have in an airport, but this is your lucky day. We had: 1) sausage, pepper, & onion; 2) vegetable (fresh eggplant, zucchini, ricotta, and basil; and 3) chicken and onion. Excellent thin crust and serious sauce. Although the slices seem expensive ($6 each), they actually are double slices, so one feeds your average appetite. Look for it in C terminal near C23.", 'date': '2019-08-05 20:03:35', 'user': {'name': 'Glenn', 'review_count': 82, 'yelping_since': '2016-04-15 21:29:22', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 3.88, 'fans': 2}}
[R21] {'review_id': 'H0rTENLDtn-K9jbxmxN7jA', 'user_id': 'qPF6bqjBQw3a2ymKmBPElg', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 3, 'text': "Gorgeous pizzas. Mushroom slice very tasty. Some of the slices may be five star worthy but I didn't get to taste everything.", 'date': '2019-07-21 22:41:35', 'user': {'name': 'Alyssa', 'review_count': 594, 'yelping_since': '2012-09-08 01:14:56', 'elite': '2018,2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.28, 'fans': 29}}
[R22] {'review_id': 'RmnffdqXTLJxWVx_GHJ_xw', 'user_id': '3L2B7tA41wKdz35VonAImA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Absolutely delicious!! I'm visiting from San Francisco, first time in Philly! I Love pizza and happened to walk by this place around gate C 24 at the airport! I'm amazed by how many different choices they have and ready to go! Very cheesy and absolutely tasty! I wish I had taken a photo of my super delicious sliced pizza before finishing it in seconds! A slice is big but it's so good that I might get another one before hopping on the plane! Love Philly!", 'date': '2019-06-16 14:57:41', 'user': {'name': 'Joanne', 'review_count': 12, 'yelping_since': '2014-01-11 17:34:25', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.0, 'fans': 4}}
[R23] {'review_id': 'lKks31gKUEMO8Ho-fAcYfg', 'user_id': '9GUuNKZinw7JxT2nG3jSmg', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'One of the best places for airport food that I have experienced.  The food is excellent. It is one of the few places with breakfast at the airport. All panini bread for sandwiches is home made. Breakfast meals are excellent and large enough to share.  At the Philadelphia Airport, it is located right across from gate C24 in concourse C. \n\nI would have rated it a five star, but the employees were arguing with each other while preparing my sandwich. That was very unprofessional. They ended up putting cheese on my sandwich when I asked for no cheese. There is a seating area, but small. They also accept euro for those returning from a trip from Europe. \n\nWe will be sure to return here when passing through the Philadelphia Airport in the future.', 'date': '2019-06-09 13:27:40', 'user': {'name': 'Kathy', 'review_count': 520, 'yelping_since': '2018-05-06 22:09:29', 'elite': '2019,20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.31, 'fans': 14}}
[R24] {'review_id': 'Z3JbN4JD4lxb86BYl2W6Bw', 'user_id': 'dccateTjyakPfsWd5U0wsQ', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Very efficient service; pizza is made daily on site and reheated at a moment's notice. It's not typical airport pizza and taste delicious. The margherita was greaseless, a thin mozzarella layer of cheese on the bottom, topped with mild tomato sauce and some some basil. Very fair for a generous slice at $4.50. \n\nIt's worth going out of the way and even if you're in a rush, I watched them for 20 minutes as I ate, every order was fulfilled within 5 minutes of ordering. don't expect perfection, but this is so close to 5 stars.", 'date': '2019-04-05 22:10:58', 'user': {'name': 'Will', 'review_count': 240, 'yelping_since': '2009-08-04 02:09:11', 'elite': '2010,2011,2012,2013,2014,2015', 'average_stars': 3.44, 'fans': 24}}
[R25] {'review_id': '2tKN4Hb9H2Km8lDihJVCKQ', 'user_id': 'ph-F9RlnjyRySZEpU0iALw', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Very tasty and friendly of abrupt fast food. Excellent pizza if hard to eat without a fork!', 'date': '2019-02-20 20:50:24', 'user': {'name': 'Keith', 'review_count': 82, 'yelping_since': '2015-08-29 20:45:41', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.96, 'fans': 0}}
[R26] {'review_id': '6Uk2bcTknivbXrLE2pJy2w', 'user_id': 'mJfPaE-Cm1j8RokdVeKFLA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': 'Terminal C.  This has to be the biggest breakfast in the airport for the money.  Scrambled egg platter with bacon is $10 and enough for two people.  Food is average in taste, but very generous which is why I added a star.', 'date': '2019-02-20 14:30:10', 'user': {'name': 'Walter', 'review_count': 56, 'yelping_since': '2011-05-16 02:30:19', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.93, 'fans': 0}}
[R27] {'review_id': 'iRjqepXLPd2h879k9K8Svg', 'user_id': 'dFbwH2lLqp10ZRKK534OAw', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'The manager was so accommodating to our dietary restrictions. The food was hot and delicious. The bacon was thick! The portion size was great for the cost! Much appreciated!', 'date': '2019-02-10 13:31:38', 'user': {'name': 'Adyna', 'review_count': 23, 'yelping_since': '2012-04-27 15:03:45', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.61, 'fans': 0}}
[R28] {'review_id': 'nlYQEMYj-hlBmDx5o7X_AA', 'user_id': 'WGGwBkOIk7qa-6SMp6gUdA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "It's a slice of pizza.  It's better than sbarro, but so is an old shoe.  \n\nNot sure why everyone is freaking out about it.  \n\nPerhaps all the food options in PHL airport really suck.  \n\nHad a slice of sausage, onion and pepper.  It was ok.  Crust was ok, toppings were ok, service was pleasant and it was quick.", 'date': '2019-01-30 21:21:07', 'user': {'name': 'Todd', 'review_count': 68, 'yelping_since': '2009-11-09 19:14:22', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.04, 'fans': 1}}
[R29] {'review_id': '4CgNCr1yidm5mgSM7y9iKA', 'user_id': 'sDfqYG2F1j1MBXdqobBDTA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Amazing pizza & wings!! I had the bell pepper, sausage and onion slice of pizza and from the cheese to the crust it was fantastic! The baked  wings are beyond delicious! Bonus the men at the counter are so delightful and pleasant. The place to eat at Philadelphia International Airport.', 'date': '2019-01-12 19:50:45', 'user': {'name': 'Rachel', 'review_count': 52, 'yelping_since': '2013-01-03 21:54:14', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.05, 'fans': 0}}
[R30] {'review_id': 'DDpBoTZar03gLPDEpfiUwA', 'user_id': 'LSoosve2WVi7uSsxK5MTVw', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "I got a chicken pest sandwitch here before a flight once and it was much better than I expected. Will try again if I'm in the terminal.", 'date': '2018-10-16 15:09:17', 'user': {'name': 'Phil', 'review_count': 14, 'yelping_since': '2009-08-27 15:03:34', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.5, 'fans': 0}}
[R31] {'review_id': '8DxgRRf3MZUVelGUnd__HQ', 'user_id': 'v-2wnODo2wGZHUFxzKO6TA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'After a very disappointing flight cancellation on Sunday, I needed a quick bite to eat as I made plans for a hotel and new flight. This restaurant had delicious pizza and the sauce was incredible. I had a slice of sausage Margherita. Staff had a good sense of humor and service was quick.', 'date': '2018-07-18 00:46:22', 'user': {'name': 'Brad', 'review_count': 10, 'yelping_since': '2018-07-15 18:36:33', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.7, 'fans': 0}}
[R32] {'review_id': 'fhGrBYKv2V7_luiav5foVQ', 'user_id': 'niFCh88RF3grA9y_RDeVvA', 'business_id': 'YBjFuFJXKBKdsxx2TlQVPw', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "In Terminal C at Philly airport, you could have another $10+ cheesesteak on your layover or a fresh, crisp salad with fresh roasted chicken for $10 from this family owned gem. Airport food is the worst but everything we tried here was surprisingly great. Cheese pizza was so yum I stole bites from my 2 year old. The cannoli was delish hours later on my flight with a cup of airline coffee. I prefer custard cannolis because I'm a snob and used to live in the North End neighborhood of Boston with access to amazing Italian food, but this was not bad at all.  I don't fly through Philly much, but if you do, this place is a big 2 thumbs up!!", 'date': '2018-06-09 13:40:57', 'user': {'name': 'Tara', 'review_count': 15, 'yelping_since': '2014-03-09 16:13:08', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 4.29, 'fans': 0}}
