[R3] {'review_id': 'AAInLliSZ5i_VIlPtD8K5Q', 'user_id': 'wACiJiJdCikLZh9CxInL6g', 'business_id': 'JbVtIpb0iKnSzlPT83KMOA', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "i've been going to liberty choice for like 8 years. i love it dearly. even when it had health code violations, i still remained a loyal customer. but for the love of gourd, please, can someone who runs this place enforce employees wearing their masks????! newsflash: walking around the entire store with your mask down and then pulling it up last second when you see a customer is NOT GOOD ENOUGH. the employees could be asymptomatic carriers, and in that case would be spreading their viral load all around the store all day every day. i'm still giving 3 stars because i really do love this business but dear lord PLEASE start taking this deadly pandemic a little more seriously. shameful", 'date': '2021-01-13 02:09:33', 'user': {'name': 'Jarls', 'review_count': 72, 'yelping_since': '2012-05-05 16:35:37', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.31, 'fans': 0}}
[R4] {'review_id': 'uSycz-xXcYZ6R1ZK2lrZwg', 'user_id': 'O_-4xX-JfhDm6S4guIPNdA', 'business_id': 'JbVtIpb0iKnSzlPT83KMOA', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 7, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I\'ve always loved and appreciated this market - great falafel, great selection of pantry ingredients, great Middle Eastern prepared foods, super friendly people. But this morning I guess marks the end of my patronage there.\n\nI had maybe 5 things in my cart - just butter and cream cheese for cake icing. The woman at the counter, who I always looked forward to seeing, told me, "I guess everybody\'s bein\' lazy now." I asked what she meant - I thought she was referring to what was in my cart. She told me that I just plopped my basket on the counter for her to unpack, and that it was rude. \n\nIt took me a while to realize that she was commenting on how people are\'t unpacking their baskets because she\'s not wearing a mask. \n\nIf you want to be polite and lay your groceries on the counter, you have to stand directly in front of a woman not wearing a mask - not even pretending to wear a mask. But if you step to the left, there\'s a plexiglass shield and you won\'t be able to lay your items on the counter from there. \n\nI told her I was just trying to stay safe. She told me it was a hoax. I told her I lost an uncle to this disease and knew many more friends who lost parents and aunts/uncles. She told me the glass protected her. We went on like that briefly and I told her it was a shame we wouldn\'t be shopping there anymore. And it is. \n\nI always enjoyed a friendly neighborly banter, sharing smiles and warmth and "Hey, seriously, I hope you have a good day" sentiment. \n\nI hate this timeline.', 'date': '2020-07-17 14:37:04', 'user': {'name': 'Rebecca', 'review_count': 47, 'yelping_since': '2010-07-02 13:22:02', 'elite': '', 'average_stars': 3.67, 'fans': 7}}
[R5] {'review_id': 'F6o7ZpwWFW7ZhW_VQXLmeQ', 'user_id': '94nuNE5-Eh8XMT7QVC_uJQ', 'business_id': 'JbVtIpb0iKnSzlPT83KMOA', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Great local market. I haven't tried the food but my fiancé tells me it's fantastic. I wanted a specific middle eastern yogurt drink and we stopped in because he said they would have it. The owner knew what I was talking about. It's not an item they usually sell but they do use it in some of their prepared foods. He went back into their kitchen and produced a half gallon jug of it and sold it to me even though it's part of their usual inventory for sale. I'm sure they would accommodate any other weird requests. The hummus and other items they prepare in house look awesome. Their grocery is more extensive and less expensive than your typical convenience store. Excellent customer service.", 'date': '2020-04-25 09:11:52', 'user': {'name': 'Megan', 'review_count': 127, 'yelping_since': '2009-10-01 00:04:58', 'elite': '20,20,2021', 'average_stars': 4.3, 'fans': 1}}
